title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour Veg-All over chicken (juice and all).
Add cream of chicken soup; spread over mixture.
Mix flour and milk; pour over this.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: cheese pseudo souffle
directions: Place bread cubes and cheese in deep casserole dish.
Mix eggs, milk and salt and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and macaroni zinger
directions: Spray a large frying pan with Pam and saute chicken, onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Mix together the soup, milk and cheese and then add this to sauteed mixture.
Add fennel seed and crushed red pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, if desired.
Add more milk if needed for smooth consistency.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake in a 275° oven about 2 hours.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water in a large, heatproof bowl, for 5 minutes.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups of the boiling water, lemon juice, sugar and salt; stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Mix the remaining 1/2 cup water with the mayonnaise in a small bowl. Mix into the gelatin mixture along with the onion until smooth and well blended.
Stir in green and red peppers, celery, cabbage and carrots.

title: beef pie casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pat meat mixture into bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Pinch 1 inch fluting around edge.
Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in blender.
Pour blended mixture into mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Nuts or raisins may be added.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: crab dressing
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Crumble cornbread into dish. Cover with sauteed mixture.
Mix well.
Crumble bread slices into mixture.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Mix by hand.
Add crab meat. Add enough water to make pliable.
Salt and pepper to taste. Spread in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream margarine, fruit sweetener, applesauce and yogurt.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine dry ingredients separately and stir into batter.
Add vanilla; add blueberries and nuts.
Spoon batter into 15 muffin cups which have been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; salt and pepper lightly.
Place in roaster; add soups and tuna.
Mix well.
Mix potato chips into mixture; garnish top with several additional whole chips.
Cover. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order as listed in large salad bowl. Wait until ready to serve before putting Doritos and cheese on top.
Serve with Western brand dressing.

title: microwave smores
directions: Place chocolate bar on 1 graham cracker.
Place marshmallows on top of chocolate bar.
Cover with remaining cracker.
Microwave on High for 15 seconds.

title: country cheddar bread with herbs
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package directions, adding dry ingredients to package mix.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Shape dough into round ball and press lightly onto greased cookie sheet.
Cover with kitchen towel and allow to rise in a warm, draft-free place for 20 minutes.

title: french fried shrimp
directions: Combine ingredients, except shrimp.
Beat well.
Dry shrimp thoroughly and remove black vein. Dip in batter.
Fry in deep hot fat at 375° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately with tartar sauce.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, margarine, water and sugar.
Add flour and stir until soft.
Fill muffin pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Cut asparagus diagonally into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Thinly slice zucchini and summer squash. Steam asparagus, squash, zucchini and broccoli for 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add carrots and peppers to onion mixture.
Saute until crisp.
Remove from heat.
Drain.
Combine broth, basil and salt in medium pan.
Cook over medium-high heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook linguine according to package directions; drain well.
Toss linguine, vegetables, broth and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: blender cheese cake
directions: Put in blender and blend for 7 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with cinnamon before serving.

title: pear jam
directions: Chip pears; cover with water and boil until tender.
Drain. Beat with mixer.
Put all ingredients in a saucepan and cook 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: onion-beef-macaroni casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Stir in soup mix, tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: recipe for love
directions: Done daily. Yields a happy mom and child.

title: seafood soup with pasta
directions: Heat olive oil in a large, wide pan over medium-low heat.
Add onion, leeks and celery; cook until tender but not brown, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and garlic; cook 1 minute. Add stock, bay leaf, saffron, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, uncovered, 20 minutes. Add tomato paste and cook 1 minute.
Discard bay leaf.

title: green beans
directions: Melt butter and brown almonds.
Add beans and leave in frypan at 250°.
Salt and pepper to taste. Leave about 1/4 can of juice.

title: sherried beef
directions: Combine and bake 2 or 3 hours at 350°.

title: cocktail reubens
directions: Spread each slice of rye with a little of the salad dressing. Top with a thin slice of corned beef.
Cover with a teaspoon of sauerkraut.
Cut each slice of cheese into 6 pieces.
Put 1 piece on each appetizer.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts and appetizers are heated through.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Heat the drippings in a heavy pan or Dutch oven.
Slice the onions and brown them in the drippings.
Then add the meat and brown it well on all sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the stock.
Peel the tomatoes and cut them into chunks; add to the meat.
Add the ginger.
Cover the pot tightly and simmer very slowly for 3 hours or until the meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix together well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: old world coffee cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Spread half into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar with a fork in a tall glass until very light and fluffy.
(If you make several servings at the same time, you may use an electric beater.)
Add orange juice or hot water and brandy.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: In small pan, cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
In small mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Add to carrots in a casserole dish and stir to combine. In a small mixing bowl, toss together crushed crackers, butter and parsley.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over carrots.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Add cheese and bake until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine strawberry jello and fruit cocktail and bring to a boil.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Stir and congeal.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in a large airtight container.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 gallons.
When using, measure 1/3 cup of mixture and finish filling cup with hot water.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender (approximately 25 minutes).
Cut potatoes into 1/8-inch slices.
Cook onion and butter in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, pepper and salt. Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Add milk and 3/4 of the cheese. Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Take the angel food cake and pinch into small pieces.
Layer the bottom of a large bowl with 1/2 of cake mix, Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar and put a layer of this over the cake.

title: sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Drain dried lima beans, green lima beans, kidney beans and pork and beans.
Mix beans, onions, bacon, sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and garlic powder together.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage ring 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and mold into a ring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Freeze.
Thaw and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt together.
Cover balls with chocolate mix.

title: yellow cake with caramel icing
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large bowl.
Add shortening and 2/3 of the milk.
Beat 2 minutes
at medium speed.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely before icing.

title: greek potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over potatoes until mixture comes up halfway. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil. Raise oven to 400° and bake until crisp and brown.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Chill.
Serve as a sauce for clams, shrimp or oysters.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: cajun chicken or turkey burgers
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Form into 4-inch patties.
Broil or grill each side for 4 to 6 minutes, depending on degree of desired doneness.

title: alma's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and beat well.
Fold in other ingredients.
Drop by spoon on foil covered cookie sheet.
Turn off oven and put cookies in.
Leave overnight.
Forget until cool.

title: italian style mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop stems very fine.
In bowl, mix all ingredients, except mushroom caps.
With chopped stems.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps.
Dip cap in olive oil 3/4 of the way up.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cornstarch custard
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour into a baking dish.
Top with a meringue.
Bake in oven at 350° until meringue is golden brown.

title: salmon bake
directions: Bake salmon steaks with onion slices, lemon juice, salt and pepper on top at 350° for approximately 25 minutes, until it breaks away easily with fork.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Cover with water the carrot, onion, garlic clove and potato. Steam until tender.
Puree in it's own water.
Steam spinach in one cup water until wilted.
Puree.
Make a roux by whisking flour and melted butter.
Whisk in milk and cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the spinach to the roux along with 1/2 to 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, basil, nutmeg, thyme and fresh herb (parsley or marjoram).
Add first mixture to second.
Adjust seasonings and if too thick add milk.
Heat and stir until smooth, creamy, green and fragrant.
Heat over very low flame.

title: co-co-not cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and coconut extract.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in Bix-Mix and spud flakes.
Cover bowl and chill for 1 hour.
Shape dough in marble size balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large kettle and boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat, but do not boil.
Pack in clean hot jars and seal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate velvet frosting
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and butter over hot, not boiling, water. Remove from water.
Add milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix until well blended.
Beat in confectioners sugar gradually.

title: crunchy chicken and rice bake
directions: In saucepan combine soup and milk; heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chicken, rice, beans, mushrooms, pimento, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Beat until smooth, about 8 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat until soft and smooth.

title: pecan squares
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: italian rolls
directions: Heat 2 cups water, boil and pour over oil, sugar and salt. Cool and put yeast in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add to cool mixture along with eggs and 1/2 of flour; stir mixture smooth.
Add rest of flour and blend well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead lightly.
Shape into rolls and place on buttered sheet.
Let rise until double, brush with egg white and add seeds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix flour, water and yeast.
Let set out overnight in bowl covered with a towel.
Next morning, add sugar, oil, salt, soda and eggs.
Stir well.
Cook on griddle coated with oil.

title: beef birds
directions: Cut steak into triangular shapes with the widest part about 5 inches.
Salt and pepper.
Wrap 1/2 piece bacon around cube of onion.
Roll meat around bacon and onion and fasten with toothpicks.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour half of batter in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While it bakes, melt caramels, oleo and milk slowly.
Spread caramel mixture over cake. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Pour on rest of cake batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and sugar in pan.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Let sugar dissolve.
Combine jello and water; stir and pour into pineapple mixture.
Stir over heat until jello dissolves. Pour into large bowl; refrigerate until it partially gels.
Prepare grated cheese and whipped cream into mixture.
Refrigerate until completely gelled.

title: olive dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise. Add nuts, olives and olive juice. Chill for 24 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute zucchini, onion, oregano, Italian seasoning, basil leaves, garlic, salt and pepper until zucchini is tender.
In a large greased casserole dish, layer zucchini, tomatoes and cheese, making as many layers as you can, ending with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix lemon juice with milk.
Add cherry filling and pineapple. Fold in well.
Add Cool Whip and almond extract.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Chill 2 hours or overnight if possible.

title: ahhh good salad
directions: Cut cabbage and onions fine. Melt margarine; add almonds and crushed noodles. Saut until light tan. Drain and cool on paper towel. Combine with cabbage and onions; pour dressing over salad. Toss well.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Let stand while mixing together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Break egg over apples; mix well.
Then mix with other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup water and eggs.
Blend well.
Add remaining water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in rum.
Chill 1/2 hour in refrigerator (not freezer).
Blend Cool Whip into chilled mixture.
Spoon into pie crust and chill for 2 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and, if you wish, you can put lime slices on top also.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with a scant 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 10 in. graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Before serving, top with cherry pie filling which has been mixed with 1/8 tsp. almond extract.
Keep refrigerated. Serves 6-8.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and mix well.
Add flour; mix well. Add oil and flavorings and beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool.

title: german apple cake (or plum or peach)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish. Combine the butter, 1 cup sugar and eggs in bowl and beat thoroughly. Add flour, baking powder and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Spread evenly in baking dish. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon.
Add to the apples, coating well. Arrange slices on top of batter in overlapping rows, pressing lightly in batter. Bake 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: no bake peanut butter crunch snacks
directions: Bring to boil sugar and Karo to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet until cool.

title: mom's bread
directions: In bowl combine water and yeast.
Add sugar, melted butter and beaten egg.
Add flour and salt.
Knead dough and let raise.
Punch down and put in 2 bread tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes depending on oven.
Brush with butter when taken from oven and pans.
Enjoy!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bone, skin and cube chicken breasts.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Spread into 2-quart (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Top with crushed potato chips and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Put into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: "no longer" dill pickles
directions: Drain liquid off pickles; throw away juice.
Rinse pickles in jar several times.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Shake well.
Put in refrigerator and store for 6 days.
Shake once or turn upside down every day.
Crisp and delicious!

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Coat meat with seasoned flour; brown in oil.
Add barbecue sauce, vinegar and water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, adding green pepper and preserves during last 15 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: peach preserves
directions: Peel, pit and finely chop peaches; measure 4 cups into a large saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice and pectin.
Let stand 10 minutes ,stirring frequently.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from heat. Stir in Equal.
Ladle into freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal and label.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours at room temperature.
Store up to 3 weeks in the refrigerator or 6 months in the freezer.
Makes about 4 cups (64 one tablespoon servings).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except
chips
and
cheese. Sprinkle cheese over top of pan, then the crushed potato chips. Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In medium bowl, beat syrup, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt with a fork until mixed.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shell and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Place on wire rack to cool.

title: chopped spinach dip
directions: Make sure spinach is drained thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients in a medium-size bowl and mix.
Chill before serving. Add Pace picante sauce, if desired.
Makes 4 servings; 1 fat gram per serving and 60 calories per serving.

title: cornflakes cookies
directions: Cream shortening or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add milk.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Add flour mixture to batter, mixing well.
Add cornflakes, coconut, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet, flatten with fork moistened with water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yields 60 cookies.

title: old-fashioned corn pone
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and 1 pint warm water.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and the soda and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Pour into greased skillet or pan.
The best results are achieved in an angel food pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.
When done, pour 1 cup boiling water over the corn pone while still in the pan or skillet.
Allow to soak in.
Serve.
It will be soft and mushy.
Recipe will feed 4 to 6.

title: haluski
directions: Mix potatoes with flour until you can work with it in your hand to make small balls.
In a large kettle, boil salted water. Drop balls into the water and boil about 10 minutes or until they come to the top.
Then drain when done.

title: sweet dough
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together.
Alternate flour mixture and milk with other ingredients.
Mix well.
If dough is too sticky, add a little more flour.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce, 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese and green and red pepper.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with bread sticks.
Makes 10 servings.

title: strudel
directions: Combine 3/4 cup melted oleo, egg yolk, warm milk and flour. Let set in refrigerator for 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out real thin.
Add apples, nuts, raisins, coconut, crushed vanilla wafers, 1/2 cup sugar and oleo drippled all over.
Roll up and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sangria
directions: Mix ingredients in punch bowl. Add cut up apples, lemons, oranges and limes. Add to punch bowl.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water with salt for 2 minutes and let sit until cool.
Carrots need to be tender.
Drain.
Combine oil, soup, mustard, vinegar, sugar and worcestershire sauce.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Pour over vegetables and let marinate over night.

title: potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil whole, until tender when pricked with a sharp knife or fork.
Remove from hot water and cover with cold water, to stop the cooking process; allow to cool.
Once cooled, scrape skins off and cut potatoes into cubes. Mix all ingredients, except paprika, with potatoes.
More mayonnaise can be added if salad is not moist enough.
Refrigerate in serving dish.
Sprinkle top of salad with paprika, for a garnish.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch round pans or two 9 inch pans. Bake at 325°for 20 - 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: mexican stew
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients, except oats.
Add dry to cream mixture.
Add oats and roll into 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight (or couple days).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Partially cook zucchini.
Mix
everything else (except grated cheese) until smooth.
Fold in vegetables and chilies and put in buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Baking time: 50 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed jalapenos
directions: Split peppers to remove seeds and pulp.
Set aside on a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan. Blend together cheeses.
Slowly add mixture into split jalapenos generously. Bake in conventional oven 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix cheeses and mayonnaise together.
Add chopped onions and artichokes and mix well.
Spread into a Quiche pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: turkey roll
directions: Unroll pizza dough. Place dough side by side on a baking sheet with two short sides touching; pinch to seal.

title: pasta ala savannah
directions: After cooking pasta, cut up vegetables (except tomato) and saute in olive oil.
Pour pasta in skillet with sauteed vegetables and stir.
Pour Italian dressing over pasta and vegetables.
Cut up tomato right before serving and put on top.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together all in one bowl.
Let chill before serving.

title: italian hunters stew
directions: About 2-1/2 hours before serving:
In large Dutch ovens, heat oil brown beef on all sides.
Add garlic and onion and saute well, stirring frequently. Stir in tomato paste, flour, chili powder, oregano, rosemary, salt, tomatoes, parsley.
Add 1 cup water. simmer, covered 1 hour 15 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Add carrots and simmer 45 minutes.
Meanwhile cook macaroni in separate pan, drain well.
Stir into stew with cheese.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: calamari-portuguese
directions: Thaw frozen squid.
Clean squid according to procedure.
Cut mantles into quarters.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in oil. Add squid, parsley, tomato paste, salt and water; cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until squid is tender.
Serve over noodles or spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Mix together pecans, walnuts, raisins, vanilla wafers, cherries and candied fruit in large bowl.
Put milk and marshmallows in boiler; heat until marshmallows melt.
Mix all ingredients; press into large Bundt pan or make into small loaves.
Cover; refrigerate 2 days before serving.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix pumpkin, oil and water together in a small bowl.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts or raisins.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 mins. at 350 degrees.

title: roman delight
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes (chopped or blended) and sugar to meat.
Simmer for 10 or 15 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Fold into noodles.
Layer noodles and meat mixture in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top (grated Parmesan cheese can always be used).
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Blend sugar, margarine, bread and eggs in a blender.
Stir in pineapple.
Place in a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef in gravy (white sauce)
directions: To make a medium white sauce, combine butter, flour, milk and salt in double boiler.
Stir with slotted spoon until flour, butter, milk and salt are stirred in and melted.
(Double recipe for more gravy.)
After white sauce has thickened, add chipped beef.
Pour over toast, corn bread or potatoes.
It's your choice.

title: carrot salad
directions: In a bowl mix carrots with orange juice to moisten.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well; then moisten with mayonnaise.

title: spiced pumpkin rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/2 teaspoon sugar in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining sugar, pumpkin and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually stir in 3 3/4 cups bread flour and whole wheat flour to make a soft dough.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons bread flour evenly over work surface.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place dough in a large bowl coated with cooking spray, turning to coat top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour and 15 minutes or until dough is doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down and divide into 24 equal portions; shape each portion into a 10-inch rope.
Tie each rope into a loose knot and place on baking sheets, coated with cooking spray.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind all together and soak overnight in 5 tablespoons salt. Drain, rinse and drain again.

title: african pickles
directions: Drain pickles; reserve juice.
Cut pickles in quarters lengthwise, then in half through middle, to get 8 pieces from each pickle, put pickles back into jar, layering with red pepper and garlic.
Dissolve brown sugar in pickle juice, holding back 1/2 cup juice which will be displaced by sugar.
Pour over pickles in jar. Let sit at room temperature 24 hours, then refrigerate before serving.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix the sugar, butter, flour, vanilla and eggs.
Fold in pecan halves and marshmallows.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: golden potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato into 10 to 12 wedges.
Place potatoes in a shallow baking pan.
Melt butter and mix with oil and add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Then pour mixture over wedges and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: peach pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and flour. Stir in syrup and salt. Mix well. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until just blended. Add peaches; pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with topping. Bake in hot oven (400°) about 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted halfway between center and edge of pie. Serve chilled.

title: "colorado cache" chocolate-peppermint bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butter. Cream eggs and sugar. Add flour and chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes. Turn oven off and bake 5 more minutes.

title: summer cake
directions: Prepare jello as directed, but omit the cold water. Do not refrigerate, let set at room temperature. Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan. Let cool. Poke holes in cake. Pour jello over all. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Frost with Cool Whip before serving.

title: rice consomme casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter in a skillet.
Add dry rice and brown. Pour soup, mushrooms and onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. After rice is browned, add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Easy and quick.
Great with hamburgers.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: nutty cheese balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Wet hands and shape into balls. Roll in pecans and chill.

title: french toast strata
directions: Break up bread; mix eggs, milk and syrup.

title: miracle whip cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients well and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stores well and stays moist.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients. Mix together and add next 3 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients. Drop on lightly greased baking sheets by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw rice in bottom of pan.
Brown pork chops.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Place sliced onion, bell pepper and tomato.
Salt and pepper.
Pour bouillon over the top and cover. Cook at 375° for 1 hour. Add water if needed.

title: patio nacho casserole
directions: In 13 x 9-inch microwave-safe baking dish, combine ground beef and onion, breaking meat apart with fork.
Microwave on High, covered with wax paper, about 5 minutes, stirring once.
Add pork and beans, corn, tomato soup and chili powder, mixing well. Microwave on High, covered with wax paper, 10 to 12 minutes, stirring twice, until thoroughly hot and bubbling.

title: old fashioned german liverwurst
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Liverwurst may be fried slowly in large frying pan or placed in small loaf pans and baked slowly (1 hour) at 350°.
Stores well in refrigerator .
Heat to serve or slice and eat cold.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown
meat in skillet over medium heat.
Drain fat and set meat aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat,
cheese, onions and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until brown on top.
Serves 6 to 8. Can be frozen.

title: "hoppin' john" black-eyed peas delicious
directions: Wash and
pick	over
peas;
cover
with water and soak overnight.	Drain.	Place
peas
in
kettle;
cover with fresh water and
season with pork jowl.
Add salt and garlic halves. Cook peas for
3 hours or until tender, adding water when more liquid is
needed.	Just
before serving, heat oil in skillet; add mashed garlic, green peppers, onions, sage and bay leaves. Cook until vegetables are soft.	Add vinegar, salt and pepper. Pour vegetable
mixture	into cooked peas.
Blend together and serve. This
dish	may be served over cooked rice for Hoppin' John.

title: my favorite chocolate cake squares
directions: Combine the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil Crisco, cocoa, margarine and water.
Pour hot mixture into flour-sugar combination.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat and pour into cookie sheet with sides (7 x 11-inch).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
In the meantime mix icing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook brown sugar, cream and butter in heavy skillet until thick and brown.
Mix together well the milk, cornstarch and egg yolks. Add to sugar mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets and slice into sterilized jars. Pour over beets the beet juice, vinegar, salt and sugar. Let come to boil. Seal jars.

title: filbert fancies
directions: Coarsely chop filberts; spread on baking sheet.
Toast in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Beat powdered sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt into beaten egg until very light and fluffy.
Add cooled chocolate.
Fold into marshmallows and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon into bowl of coconut; roll evenly to coat.
Place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Stir in the flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Gradually add milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from the heat; stir in cheese until melted. Add potatoes and onion; stir well. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover; bake 30 to 40 minutes longer or until the potatoes are tender. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: jiffies
directions: Break crackers into small pieces. Add milk and chocolate bits. Add nuts and mix well. Bake in square pan at 250° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to the first 4 ingredients.
Toss frequently.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 5.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Pick chicken off of bone. Prepare stuffing mix as directed.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops off of bell peppers; remove inside.
Put in cold water and bring to boil.
Let boil 3 or 4 minutes; remove and drain.
Saute onions, shallots and minced garlic in the butter. Add meat and brown.
Add rice, mushrooms with liquid, cheese, seasoning and bread crumbs.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, working quickly; return to heat for 5 minutes.
Fill peppers; sprinkle with prepared bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
After bell peppers are cooked, a slice of cheese can be melted on top, or peppers can be topped with a cheese sauce.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook to soft ball stage sugar, butter and syrup (238°).
Remove from heat and add soda, salt and cream of tartar, mixing with wooden spoon.
Immediately pour over popped corn and mix well. Pour equal amounts on three cookie sheets with sides.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Spread out on foil or wax paper to cool.
Store in tight container.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in butter in a large skillet until crisp-tender; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until all liquid evaporates.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: blueberry drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening until soft and gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs and lemon rind. Beat until well mixed.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Slightly fold in blueberries. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: microwave breakfast ring
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in a 1 1/2-quart round baking dish. Microwave on High 1 minute or until butter melts.
Stir in nuts. Cut each biscuit into 4 equal pieces.
Arrange over sugar mixture. Stir to coat each piece.
Move mixture to edges.
Place a custard cup upside down in the center of the dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, rotating every minute.
Remove.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Invert on a serving plate and serve immediately.

title: hamburg vegetable soup
directions: Fill a 6-quart cooking pot 1/2 full of cold water.
Crumble 1/4 pound of lean hamburg into the water.
Bring to a boil and add all of the other ingredients listed.
Reduce to simmer and cook, covered, for 2 hours.
Add salt, pepper and whatever else you want while soup is cooking.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to directions for empty crust.

title: fiesta dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare taco seasoning.
Mix with ground beef and water according to package.
Add refried beans and heat 5 minutes.
In 1-quart bowl spread beef and bean mixture.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve immediately.
(I make mine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.)
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with nachos.

title: barbecued rack of lamb
directions: Rub lamb on all sides with mixture of the seasonings six hours or longer before cooking.
Cook at 350° over indirect heat in covered barbecue for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Scramble sausage and cook.
Place in pie crust.
Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water.
Drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Melt cheese in onion mixture.
Stir in mushrooms, soup and broccoli.
Serve in a crock-pot.
Makes 1 1/2-quarts.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Boil water.
Pour into the meal and flour until it's wet good.
The hot water will make it swell.
Add enough milk to make a nice batter.
Fry in hot oil until it's brown on both sides.
Mighty good with fish.
You can double or triple this recipe.

title: microwave cheese & spinach crustless quiche
directions: Beat
eggs
with
half and half until light and fluffy. Blend in	cheese, spinach, bacon, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Cook at Medium 10 to 13 minutes.
Quiche
is
done when knife inserted near center comes out
clean.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cut into 10 wedges to serve.

title: lemonade ice cream pie
directions: Prepare two Oreo Crumb pie crusts as directed on pkg; place in freezer.
In a mixing bowl combine ice cream, lemonade and 3/4 tub of whipped topping, stir until completely blended.
Spread one half into each crust.
Top with remaining whipped topping; cover air tight with foil or plastic; freeze until firm at least 4 hours.
Garnish with thinly sliced lemon, mint leaves or lemon leaves.
Place raspberries, blueberries and strawberries on plate; sprinkled with powdered sugar or Oreo crumbs.
Make 2 pies.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion; drain.
Cook macaroni in boiling water.
Mix pizza sauce with macaroni and meat.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish, alternating layers with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Chop cranberries and pecans.
Mix together all ingredients.
Let chill in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: hidden valley bacon and cheddar dip
directions: Mix dip with sour cream. Add bacon bits and cheese. Mix together and serve with crackers or bread pieces.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oblong dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; add to warm butter, then put peaches and juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until brown.

title: tropical cake
directions: Bring to boil the first 5 ingredients.	Remove from stove and add the next 4 ingredients.
Put a layer of whole graham crackers in baking dish; pour 1/2 mixture over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers.
Pour remaining filling.	Add another layer of graham crackers.

title: hot spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Lightly coat a large nonstick skillet with nonstick spray and warm over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, stirring for 5 minutes or until soft. Stir in the spinach and cook for 5 minutes or until heated through. Reduce the heat to low and stir in the cream cheese and sour cream just until blended and smooth. Stir in the Parmesan and artichokes until blended. Remove from the heat and stir in the salt, black pepper and red pepper flakes. Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart microwaveable bowl and top with the Monterey Jack. Microwave on High power for 2 to 3 minutes or just until the cheese is melted. Serve warm. Makes 5 cups (twenty 1/4-cup servings).

title: frosted grapes
directions: In small bowl, beat egg white until frothy.
Place sugar in shallow dish.
Hold each cluster of grapes by stem and dip into egg white, shaking off excess egg white.
Roll grapes in sugar until evenly coated.
Refrigerate on rack until coating is set or overnight.
Try grapes of different colors mixed to make table arrangement.
Small clumps are attractive garnish.

title: punch
directions: If you are making red punch, use the ingredients listed.
Pour in pineapple juice, 1 box cherry jello, 1 package cherry Kool-Aid and 1 can frozen orange juice.

title: chiffon fruit salad
directions: Mix hot syrup and Jell-O.
Chill until it begins to thicken. Add celery, nuts and mayonnaise.
Add to Cool Whip and chopped peaches.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel eggplant, cut in pieces and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Make cream sauce with butter, flour and milk.
When thick, add eggplant, cheese, crumbs, onion, catsup, seasonings and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture. Pour into buttered casserole and bake in 350° oven until knife comes out clean.
Garnish top with crisp, crumbled bacon, if desired.

title: christmas sugarplums
directions: Fill with cream cheese and 1 nut apiece.
Close and roll in powdered sugar.

title: skewer beef
directions: Unroll the entire flank steak.
Trim off fat.
Cut into 1/8 inch slices across the grain.
Marinate at least 4 hours, stirring sliced beef on bamboo skewers like ribbon candy.
Barbecue over charcoal or set oven to broil.
Brown 4 inches away from broiler for just a few minutes, turning over once to brown both sides.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Boil whole squash in salted water until almost tender.
Remove tops to make cavities for stuffing.
Scoop out stringy insides and discard.
Drain water that collects.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add grated onion, cheese, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, granulated sugar and 2 tablespoons of the cocoa into a large bowl.
Add the milk, butter and vanilla; mix only until smooth. Stir in the nuts, then transfer to a buttered 1-quart (10 x 6-inch) baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle over the top of the chocolate mixture. Pour boiling water over all; do not stir in!!
Bake for 40 minutes, or until the top appears to be firm.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serve warm, pudding side up, or over ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: spicy cranberry punch
directions: In
small
saucepan
melt cinnamon
candies
in
water; chill. At serving time, combine candy liquid and fruit juices in punch bowl.
Stir to dissolve frozen juices.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Makes 2 or 3 loaves.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: gourmet french dressing
directions: In blender, blend until smooth.

title: boiled brown sugar frosting
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 3 minutes gently.
Cool.
Add sugar. Beat well.
Great on chocolate cake.

title: heavenly salad(green goop)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows.
Cook over hot water or on very low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are mostly melted.
Remove from heat; add pineapple and cool.
Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Let set in refrigerator.
(May need to stir occasionally.)

title: paris potatoes
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, cottage cheese and sour cream together in casserole dish.
Top with cheddar cheese and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together, cover and chill.
Especially good with strawberries and melon.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and combine the juice with Tang and pudding.
Drain juice from other fruits and discard.
Fold all fruits into pudding mixture; chill until ready to serve.

title: apple strudel
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; let stand in oven 1/2 hour. Add the butter; knead in dough.
Slap on table several times until it forms blisters.
Roll dough on cloth from center out; stretch if necessary.
Brown bread crumbs in a pan with butter until light brown.
Spread on dough; fill with apples, raisins, sugar and cinnamon.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon on top.
Roll into a Strudel.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until light brown.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook the raisins in water until all the water is absorbed. One at a time, add applesauce, eggs, sweetener, oil and vanilla and mix well.
In separate dish, mix all dry ingredients, then add this to applesauce mixture.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion in skillet.
Mix with noodles.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, 2 cans milk and seasoning from stuffing. In a separate bowl, mix stuffing with 2 cups milk. Let set for 5 minutes. Grease lasagne pan. Add 1/2 of stuffing. Layer with meat, then add remaining stuffing. Cover with soup mixture. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes. Great for using up Thanksgiving leftovers!

title: peanutty pretzels
directions: Melt almond bark using double boiler.
Add other ingredients. Mix well and spoon into peanut shaped candy molds or on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice
and parboil squash in salted water until tender. Drain well.
Combine
chicken
soup,
water
chestnuts,
sour cream, pimentos
and
onion
and mix thoroughly.
Add squash. Mix together
margarine
and
herb stuffing; pack stuffing in bottom of
2 quart casserole, reserve enough for the topping. Pour squash over stuffing.
Top squash with reserved stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Beat well and bake in muffin tins at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease a bundt pan.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, and brown sugar. Place mixture in a plastic bag, then shake all the biscuit pieces well.
Pour come of the chopped nuts in the bottom of the bundt pan.
Layer about 1/2 the cut pieces.
Melt butter and add the remaining sugar mixture.
Pour part of this mixture over the pieces in the bundt pan.
Place the remaining pieces in the pan and pour the remaining butter over the top.
Sprinkle with the remaining nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with ripple cut potato chips.

title: tomato chutney
directions: Wash and drain fruits and vegetables.
Scald, core and peel tomatoes.
Core and pare apples.
Peel onions; remove seeds from peppers.
Chop fruits and vegetables.
Mix all ingredients and boil until thick.
Pour, boiling hot, into hot jars and seal at once.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Juice the lemons and for an extra tart taste, also grate the peel.
In a medium size bowl, combine apple juice, lemon juice, lemon peel and honey.
Freeze until solid, about 3 or 4 hours. Using a spatula, break the frozen sherbet into chunks.
In a food processor, blend the chunks until smooth and creamy.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from broth and let stand until cool enough to handle.
Remove skin, bones and excess fat. Cut chicken into small bits.
Allow broth to cool and fat to congeal on top.
Remove and discard fat according to your cholesterol count.
The more fat you can use, the better your dish will taste.
Place chicken back in broth and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and add Never Fail Dumplings (which are located in this cookbook).

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dip hot dogs in batter and deep fry.

title: tuna salad
directions: Blend all together in blender (or food processor works nicely) and put in small bowl; chill 3 hours.
Serve on crackers or vegetables.

title: pasta salad delight
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and cool.
Chop first 6 ingredients and add to spaghetti.
Pour dressing and Salad Supreme over all and mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: steak with ham-and-mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms, ham, onion and garlic in olive oil until onion is tender.
Add salt, oregano and pepper.
Stir in brandy and simmer 1 minute; set aside.
Grill steak over coals 20 to 25 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Pour sauce over steak before serving.
Yield:
2 to 5 servings.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Put the elderberries in unbaked pie crust.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; put over the berries.
Bake at 350° to 400°.

title: ort chicken kiev style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound breasts very thin.
Spread with 1/4 cup softened margarine and set aside.
Blend 1/2 cup margarine with herbs and set aside in small saucepan.
Place a cheese stick in center of each chicken breast; roll up like jelly roll.
Coat rolls with flour; dip in eggs, then bread crumbs.
Arrange in well buttered pan in single layer.
Melt margarine-herb blend and spoon over chicken.
Scatter mushrooms.
Bake 20 minutes.
Pour wine over and bake 20 minutes more.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into balls.
Make 4 small or 2 large.
Roll in crushed pecan pieces.

title: chili cheese dip(microwave recipe)
directions: Cook onion and bacon on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook for 6 to 7 minutes on power level "8".
Serve with Fritos or Doritos.

title: mayonnaise muffins (or biscuits)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop into greased muffin tin.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 to 10 minutes (until light brown).
Makes 12 muffins.
Use light mayonnaise and skim milk for low-calorie, low-fat muffins.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in glass dish with cover.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook sausage and onion in a large skillet, breaking sausage into small pieces, drain.
Combine meat with pizza sauce, spaghetti, mushrooms, olives and 1 cup of shredded Provolone cheese.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes then remove from the oven and add remaining cheeses.
Bake an additional 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: corn bread dressing (chicken)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in chicken broth and mix well (let it be moist).
Bake in 375° oven about 35 to 45 minutes until brown.
I cook my onions and celery before I mix them with the rest.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, 7-Up and ginger ale, then add vanilla ice cream, then add rainbow sherbet.
Serve.

title: ruth barney's zucchini pie
directions: Combine in large bowl biscuit mix, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Beat together eggs, oil and bitters.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and onions.
Mix well.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate or 9-inch round baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix vegetables, mayonnaise, onion, chestnuts and cheese.
Put in a casserole and crumble Ritz crackers on the top.
Melt butter and pour over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° until it is bubbly and hot through.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Simmer vinegar, water, lard and spices for about 10 minutes. Add cabbage and apples.
Cover.
Cook over low heat for about one hour.
Serve.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: red beans & rice
directions: Cook overnight in crock pot.
If cooking on stove, soak beans overnight before cooking.
Serve over cooked rice with garlic bread.

title: chocolate chip caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Hand-mix cake mix, remaining evaporated milk, butter and nuts.
Spread half of cake mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for six minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with melted caramels. Sprinkle on chocolate chips and top with remaining cake batter. (Will be difficult, as cake batter is thick.
Easiest to drop by small spoonfuls.)
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake! Brownies should be soft.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs and stir in other ingredients except broccoli and beat well.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Add to egg mixture. Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen or chickens in a pot of salted water.
Cool, strip meat off and save broth.
This may be done the day before.

title: pasta salad
directions: Blanch vegetables.
Cook and drain pasta.
Add the rest of the ingredients to taste.
Toss mandarin orange segments into pasta salad.

title: herb-cheese dip
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble.
In a four-cup glass measure, soften cream cheese.
Stir in sour cream, remaining ingredients and the bacon.
Heat 30 to 40 seconds in microwave oven before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: seasoned corn on the cob
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove husks from corn.
In a 13 x 9 baking pan combine lemon juice, soy sauce, pepper, and garlic. Add corn and toss to coat thoroughly.
Bake for 30 minutes or until corn is cooked.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together except for cheese and chips.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 450° oven. Serves 10 to 12.

title: squash pickles
directions: Stir salt into water in very large bowl, or divide between 2 bowls.
Add squash, weight down with a plate and unopened can to keep pickles under brine.
Let stand 3 hours.
Combine sugar, vinegar and mustard seed in large kettle.
Bring to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add drained squash, onions, pepper and pimientos.
Return just to boiling.
Cool, transfer to container with tight lid.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several weeks. Or place in clean hot jars and process 5 to 10 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in hot water.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze in 1/2 gallon containers.
Thaw partially and break into punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale or 7-Up over.
It's like slush; very good.
Make flavor for whatever color you need.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain liquid from all fruit.
Mix well together.
Fold in enough "Cool Whip" to hold together.
Chill and serve.

title: sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, 1/4 cup sugar and salt in bowl. Cool to lukewarm; add yeast and stir.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour to milk mixture and beat until smooth.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Meanwhile, combine 6 tablespoons melted butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Roll out dough to 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter; combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over dough.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1-inch slices; arrange in pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan and drain, reserving drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add potatoes, celery, onion, salt, thyme, pepper and reserved liquid from clams to bacon drippings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
In a 1-quart container with lid, add flour to milk.
Shake well.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium, heat 15 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently.
Stir in clams; heat gently, do not boil.
Garnish with bacon.
Makes 4 (1 1/4 cup) servings.

title: gingerbread man
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use enough flour to make stiff and easy to handle.
Refrigerate.
Flour hands to handle.
Make balls and roll out and cut with gingerbread man cutter.
Place on pan.
Have parts barely touching, they spread out.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350°, 13-15 minutes.
Remove quickly from pan.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and hang on tree to soften.
Then eat.

title: white hawaii
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: jingle bell fudge
directions: Combine in top of double boiler the butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Place over hot, not boiling, water until butterscotch melts.
Remove from water.
Stir until blended.
Add milk and stir until well blended.
Spread in foil lined pan (8 x 8-inch).
Press chopped nuts into surface.
Chill until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish, cover with cheese and melted butter, cover and bake 45 minutes at 350 F.

title: mystery squares
directions: Mix ingredients and spread over.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Boil onions (cut into rings) in salted water until done.
Drain.
Put 2 cups onions into pie crust.
Beat eggs and cream.
Put half of mixture over onions.
Then cover with cheese.
Repeat; onions, egg mixture and cheese.
Top either with pie crust or buttered bread crumbs.

title: crab and asparagus soup(sup mang tay)
directions: Boil stock in a medium saucepan over high heat.
Add the crab meat, corn, asparagus, m.s.g., salt and pepper to stock.
Cook about 10 minutes over high heat.
Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook approximately 10 minutes, skimming occasionally.
Mix cornstarch and water in a small bowl and add it to the simmering soup.
Stir until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Serve very hot.
Makes 6 small bowls.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt and cool chocolate. Sift together dry ingredients. Beat eggs until thick and creamy. Add sugar, oil, chocolate, zucchini and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix together; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Toss together onion, tomatoes and cheese.
Add dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Add corn chips, sliced avocado and beef.
Toss with beans and salt.

title: apple dijon pork roast
directions: Trim any visible fat from pork.
Cut roast in half.
Place halves side by side in a crock-pot.
Mix together the apple juice, chicken broth and mustard.	Pour mixture over pork and cover.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until a cooking thermometer reaches 160° when inserted into each piece.
Remove meat to a platter. Using 2 forks, shred the meat.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water and stir until dissolved, then mix with sauce in the crock-pot a tablespoon at a time to prevent lumping.
When mixture is smooth, pour over shredded meat and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pie dish.
Spread Hormel chili on cream cheese.
Spread green chilies next.
Last spread shredded cheese as top layer.
Bake in oven at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and serve with tortilla chips.

title: marinade for steak
directions: Marinate steak for 12 to 24 hours.
Because of the soy sauce the steak can be salty, but it's great!

title: beef burgundy(4 servings)
directions: Slice beef into thin bite-sized strips.
In 2-quart pan cook half of beef in half of oil.
Repeat with rest of beef and oil. Return all beef to pan.
Stir in cornstarch.
Add next 8 ingredients and cook over low heat 35 to 45 minutes until tender. Add mushrooms 5 minutes before end of cooking time.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot rice.

title: glorious macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Saute onion and pimiento in butter until onion is crisp-tender.
Combine macaroni, onion mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: no cook dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix, 1 cup milk and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Add remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and pudding mix.
Blend at low speed.
Beat on high speed minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vanilla crisps
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and salt. Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
(Or chill dough; shape into 1-inch balls.)
Flatten with floured glass. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool on rack.
Makes 84.

title: mexican wedding cake(and frosting)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an UNGREASED 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow to cool before frosting.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, vanilla and potatoes.
In a saucepan melt oleo; add marshmallows and mix until melted.
Pour into potato mixture, stirring as you pour.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns in microwave.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Note:
Add crushed corn flakes to top.)
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch dish in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rice, raisin, applesauce pudding
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in baking pan.
Mix rice, sugar, milk, applesauce, 1 stick oleo (melted ) and eggs (well beaten), then add raisins.
Pour into baking pan of which butter has been melted.
Bake until set and lightly brown in 375° to 400° oven. Don't overbake.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, eggs, onions, celery, salt, milk, pepper, herb seasoned bread crumbs and 1/2 cup ketchup in bowl; mix well. Press into greased loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar, remaining 1/4 cup ketchup, nutmeg and mustard; mix well.
Spoon over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until center is brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor or blender; mix with 1 cup sugar.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Mix Dream Whip and add to cranberries.
Drain all fruit.
Add all other ingredients. This recipe may be doubled for large crowd.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Lay asparagus in bottom of a casserole dish and place chicken breasts on top.
In a saucepan, combine butter, flour, chicken broth and milk and simmer.
Slowly add cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Pour over the asparagus and chicken.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 30 minutes.
Crush almonds, sprinkle on top and brown slightly.

title: herb marinated tomatoes(about 4 servings)
directions: Arrange tomato slices on a platter, sprinkle with basil, parsley and oregano.
Combine lemon juice and vinegar, drizzle over tomatoes.
Cover and chill - 2 hours.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool, right side up, for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add rest of ingredients, except nutmeg. Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until a knife inserted half way between center and edge comes clean, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country club squash
directions: Cut and cook squash until tender.
Mash.
Add salt, pepper, butter, bouillon and water.
Add egg and sour cream.
Pour in 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs, grated cheese and paprika.
Sprinkle on top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double cabbage tsukemono
directions: Chop both kinds of cabbage to about 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Put into a pan and add salt.
Let stand 30 to 60 minutes.
After setting, squeeze the vegetables out.
In a small pot, bring to a boil the brown sugar, vinegar and shoyu.
Cool the sauce a little and pour over the vegetables.

title: mother's blueberry gingerbread
directions: Set oven at 350°.

title: rice patties
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour and eggs.
Form into patties.
Dip patties in beaten eggs and coat with flour.
Fry in a hot, oiled skillet.
Brown both sides.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Add salt. Gradually add milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add soup and chicken.
Mix well.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
To this mixture add part of the milk, enough to make a medium paste.
Beat in eggs; add remaining milk.
Cook until very thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut. Let cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Dream Whip, chocolate syrup and pecans.

title: rum cake
directions: Add all ingredients and beat ten minutes.
Grease tube pan and dust with flour.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over bottom of pan, then pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: iris' dirty rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper, garlic and celery.
The amount of these will depend on the amount of rice you are fixing.
Add to this desired meat.
Cook until done, then add water to a bouillon to season and add pepper to taste.
Simmer until flavors blend.
Pour over rice and mix well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze water from it.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into bite size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 X 13 baking pan.
Add graham crackers.
Mix and pat down.
Add ingredients in layers in order listed.
Bake at 350 for about 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Cream the butter and 1	1/2
cups sugar until light and add the egg yolks and pineapple.
Beat for 3 minutes, then add the lemon juice, salt and egg
whites.	Pour
a
layer	into a loaf mold which has been lined
with
the
sponge cake.	Add a layer of the cake and then
the rest of the pineapple mixture. Cover with the remaining sponge cake and chill in refrigerator for 24 hours. Unmold and cover with whipped cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: granny greiner's dandelion wine
directions: Pour hot water over blossoms in crock and let stand overnight. Next day, strain and pour liquid back in the crock with 3 pounds sugar and 2 lemons, sliced thin.
Then take a slice of wet bread, sprinkle yeast on it and put on top of hot liquid.
Cover and let stand for four weeks; strain and bottle.
Do not cap too tight until through working.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix in green chilies and refried beans. Add taco seasoning mix to your taste.
Layer sour cream over meat mixture.
Top with chopped tomato, lettuce, cheese and black olives.
Dip with taco chips.

title: savory appetizer franks
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients, except hot dogs. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add hot dogs.
Simmer 15 minutes longer.
To serve, keep warm in fondue pot or chafing dish.
Makes approximately 50.

title: smoked haddock
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry until tender the mushrooms, onion, pepper, tomatoes and peas.
Place haddock and rice in large casserole.
Add fried vegetables and 2 cups cheese sauce.
Mix well and bake, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn for 50 people
directions: Add cracker crumbs, salt and pepper to taste to butter or bacon fat.
Mix milk with corn.
Place alternate layers of corn and cracker crumbs in greased pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook over medium heat until it forms a ball.
Take out on wax paper and knead it well.
Great for big and little people to play with.

title: cordon blue
directions: Place chicken in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Add next 3 ingredients in order.
Combine soup and water; mix well.
Add to casserole.
Toss stuffing mix and melted butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in greased casserole.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.

title: party potatoes
directions: Pare and boil potatoes until tender; mash.
Beat together cream cheese (softened) and sour cream.
Add the hot potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Spoon into buttered casserole and brush with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead and put in oven just before serving time.
(Reheat leftovers in microwave.)

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve in hollowed, round Hawaiian bread loaf.
Dip with crackers or cut up an extra loaf in small cubes to use for dipping.

title: apple bread
directions: In a large bowl, cream shortening, 1 cup sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in milk and vanilla. Then add apples.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on batter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: bacon corn bread
directions: *If strips are extremely narrow, I use more.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and remaining ingredients together.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Mix well, bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let cool in pan.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Make cake as directed.
Cool.
Leave in pan.
Pour Kahlua over cake.
Puncture holes so Kahlua seeps in cake.
Mix pudding as directed and chill.
In large clear glass bowl, layer 1/2 cake pieces, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 candy.
Repeat with remaining halves, ending with Cool Whip.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion; add chili.
Spread mixture in 2-quart flat casserole.
Spread with sour cream.
Layer with cheese.
Sprinkle with crushed corn chips.
Bake at 400° 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: easy cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Chop onions and tops.
Mix together with peas. Beat sour cream and Miracle Whip together.
Add to other ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: skillet franks n noodles
directions: In skillet, brown frankfurters and onion with basil in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir now and then.

title: jack's favorite pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly; then drain.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides, sealing to make the crust.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, mushrooms, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook together for 10 minutes.
Add chili beans, tomatoes and Chili-O mix.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Garnish with cheese or sour cream.
Great with macaroni.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Pour into large greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook potatoes, parsley, carrot, onion and celery (not chopped) in soup kettle until potatoes are tender.
Remove celery stalk.
Mash potatoes with a fork (coarsely).

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan or mold. Freeze.
May be served frozen or allowed to thaw.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in bottom of pan the coconut and nuts.
Make cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Drop this mixture over cake batter here and there. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until done.

title: easy four step punch
directions: Pour 7-up soda into a large bowl or punch bowl.
Add Hawaiian Punch juice and sugar; mix well.
Add slices of lemons and oranges on the top.
Add ice last.
Makes enough for 15 to 20 people.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in small glass casserole dish.
Combine 2 cups mayonnaise and 1 small carton sour cream with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place on top of salad.
Seal edges with mayonnaise mixture.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days if seal is not disturbed.

title: salmon salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: ham and herb vegetable dip
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until well chilled.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice 5 or 6 medium size Vidalia onions, not too thin.
Saute in 1 stick butter until limp, but not brown.
Separate slices with fork and layer with Ritz cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. In saucepan, combine and heat milk, Cheez Whiz, soup and butter. Heat until cheese dissolves.
Place rice over broccoli, then pour the heated ingredients on.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg white cookies
directions: Beat egg white stiff; add sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Cover pecans good; form into small cookies and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cookies in oven for 30 more minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a saucepan, bring peaches to a boil.
Add sugar to taste. Mix flour, sugar and milk in bowl.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan, then pour flour mixture into pan and then peaches.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings at joints.
Place in a large bowl.
Combine the oil, soy sauce, ginger, lemon juice and garlic.
Pour over chicken wings.
Marinate wings several hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Discard marinade.
Bake wings at 350° for 45 minutes.
Increase heat to 450° and bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 20 to 25 people as a party appetizer.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Mix together milk, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Layer cake, Cool Whip mixture and strawberry mixture.
Repeat.
Chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Serves 20 to 25.
Preparation time:
1/2 hour. Bon Appetit!

title: art's pudding(weight watchers)
directions: Mix yogurt with pineapple.
Stir in pudding powder and mix well.
Cool well in 4 dishes.
Very quick to make.

title: spicy applesauce mold
directions: Dissolve
candies
and	gelatin
in boiling water.
Add applesauce	and vinegar;
chill.
Makes 6 servings.
Good with ham or pork.
Pour into ring mold and chill.
Unmold and fill center with cottage cheese mixed with chopped celery and nuts.

title: italian sausage and mushrooms
directions: Fry sausage; cool.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices; put aside. Drain fat from pan.
Fry the mushrooms or saute the canned ones. Put in wine; let the alcohol burn off.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook until fairly thick.
Add seasonings.
Add all ingredients together. Let it set overnight.
Heat before serving.
Stir frequently. Serves 25.

title: taco bites
directions: Fry taco shells until golden brown and hard.
Place on paper towel to drain.
Coat by sprinkling with Sugar and Cinnamon Mixture.
Let sit 5 to 10 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces. Serve.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Use enough graham crackers to make 9-inch pie shell crushed and mixed with butter and press in pie plate.
Let cream cheese set out until soft, or put in microwave on defrost if you are in a hurry. Mix pudding as directed on box.
Add softened cream cheese.
Whip really good; stir in pineapple.
Pour in pie shell.
Chill.
Should be fluffy and also may be soft; still tastes good.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and powdered sugar.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, alternately with flour.
Add almond extract.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Made into layers of plain cake.
Bake at 350° (modern stove).

title: quick cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 9 X 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: caraway cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Remove bay leaves; sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: maggie valley rolls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and boiling water until margarine dissolves.
Add eggs. Dissolve yeast into 1 cup warm water.
Add to mixture.
Combine salt and flour in large mixing bowl. Gradually add already combined mixture to flour slowly.
