Mix well. Cover and put in icebox overnight.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs to mixture and beat 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Cut cake into 3 layers.
Mix strawberries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Let this mixture stand at least 1 hour.
Add whipping cream and vanilla.
Put between layers and on top and sides of cake at least an hour before serving.
Keep in refrigerator after iced.
Serves 12.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: Combine melted oleo and Heinz 57 sauce in saucepan; fill empty 57 bottle with water and add to mixture.
Add vinegar, mustard and brown sugar.
Heat and simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy yogurt potato salad
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients. Add potatoes and onions. Toss to coat well. Cover and chill 4 hours. Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Makes about 4 cups.

title: depression cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine raisins, water, sugar, butter, cinnamon and allspice in a large saucepan or Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Cook for 2 or 3 minutes, then set aside to cool. When cool, stir in the flour and baking soda. If mixture seems too thick compared to regular cake batter, add a little more water, a teaspoon at a time. Pour batter into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Yield: 8 servings.

title: beignets
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add milk mixture, 2 cups flour, egg, 2 tablespoons oil and nutmeg to yeast mixture; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.

Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk. Punch down dough; turn out onto a well floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 3 minutes).
Roll dough into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle; cut into 3 x 2-inch rectangles.

Place 1 inch apart on a lightly floured surface; cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk. Pour oil to depth of 3 to 4 inches into a large Dutch oven; heat to 375°.
Fry dough, a few pieces at a time, 1 minute on each side or until golden.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yield:
3 dozen.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all and make meatballs.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake per box instructions in 2 layers. Cool completely. Cut each layer into two.
Mix sour cream and sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line a baking dish with a little of the margarine.
Put the stuffing mix with seasoning packet into a bowl and mix with the margarine which has been about 1/2 melted.
Mix until crumbs are moist.
Layer 1/3 of crumb mixture,

1/2 of the chicken, celery soup diluted with 1 can broth, 1/3 crumbs, 1/2 chicken, chicken soup diluted with 1 can broth and top with the remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: chop suey cake
directions: In a large bowl (do not use mixer or food processor), combine flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda, pineapple with juice, walnuts and coconut.
Mix with wooden spoon until thoroughly moistened and combined.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cake is puffed and browned on top.

title: shrimply divine dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with the rest of the ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Great with fresh vegetables, small crackers and chips.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip
in a bowl.
Dump into crust.
Chill a couple of hours and enjoy.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer and spread evenly. Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 34.

title: chicken mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup broth.
Dissolve in 1/2 cup hot broth.
Combine all ingredients, except the whipped cream, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart mold.
Serve with crackers.
Can also be chilled in individual molds and used as a salad course.

title: caramel pops
directions: Put Corn Pops in large turkey roaster or deep pan.
Use heavy saucepan and wooden spoon.
Mix all other ingredients.
Heat on high heat; bring to boil.
(Do not turn heat down.)
Boil for 10 to 20 minutes, until it turns paper bag brown.
Pour over pops until coated.
Dump onto waxed paper or clean countertop until cooled.

title: kielbasa and cabbage soup
directions: In a 3-quart pan, place water, bouillon cubes, potato and onion.
Cover and boil to dissolve bouillon, stirring occasionally. Stir in cabbage, kielbasa and next three spices.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Mix 3 tablespoons powdered sugar and the rest of the apricot nectar juice.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand until well blended. Pour into well-greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly stir in vinegar.
Add lemon juice, water, raisins and butter or melted ham fat.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Serve hot with baked ham.

title: roast pork
directions: Cut deep slices on the top of pork; put salt, garlic and oregano in the slices.
Pour the juice from the sour oranges all over and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.
Place pork in pan with all the juices; cover with foil and cook on 300° for 1 hour, then remove foil.
Continue to cook until roast is tender.

title: speedy sausage macaroni dinner
directions: Reserve 12 sausage links for top of pan.
Cut remaining links diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine sliced sausage, macaroni with cheese sauce, onion and mustard in large, shallow skillet. Mix; cover.
Bring to serving temperature, stirring carefully several times during heating.
Heat remaining sausage links in skillet or hot water as directed on package.
Arrange links on top of heated macaroni.
Cut American cheese in half diagonally. Garnish top of sausage links with overlapping cheese and tomato slices.
Let stand just until cheese softens.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, lemon juice and apples.
Spoon into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until brown.
Pie will resemble pecan pie in color.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup softened butter. Mix well and press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Roll in shape with hands.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top after cookies cool.

title: herbed potatoes and carrots
directions: Place vegetables on a 24 x 18-inch piece of double thickness heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients and add ice cubes on top.
Wrap foil securely.
Cover and grill packet 3 to 5 inches from medium coals for 20 to 25 minutes, turning once, until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cornish hen casserole
directions: About 40 minutes before serving:
Preheat oven to 400°. With knife or kitchen shears, cut each hen lengthwise in half. Combine frozen green beans with spaetzle and 1 cup water in a 13
x 9-inch baking dish; arrange Cornish hen halves, cut side down,
on vegetables.
Bake,	uncovered,
30 minutes or until Cornish
hens and vegetables are heated through.	Garnish with parsley.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In one bowl, combine oatmeal and raisins. Mix well to separate raisins.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat the margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie, 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack. Store tightly covered.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of tea.

title: snappy cheese
directions: Put garlic, onion and cheese through grinder.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Stir in enough beer or milk to make spreading consistency.

title: maple fudge
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook until a soft ball may be formed.
Add nutmeats.
Beat until smooth, then pour into buttered dish.
Let cool, then cut.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix water and yeast.
Stir in sugar, oil and egg.
Add flour; dough is very sticky.
Does not need to rise.
Bake in ungreased muffin pan until golden brown.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter bottom of pan with 2 teaspoons of butter.
Spread coconut and pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecan mix.
Melt butter and cream cheese; add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ma parrish's cookies
directions: Roll on floured board.
Cut.
Bake at 350° until done.
You may sprinkle with sugar or ice with your favorite icing.

title: mustard vegetable dip
directions: Place ingredients in food processor or blender and whip until well blended.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplants a few minutes to soften inside only.
Cut in half and scoop out pulp; set aside.
Saute onion in butter briefly.
Mix onion with eggplants, crabmeat, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Add stuffing mix, enough to stick together.
If needed, moisten with cream.
Try not to break lumps of crab meat or chunks of eggplants.
Mound in eggplant halves. If desired, top with a deli-thin slice of Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve with favorite sauce.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into mold or pan.
Add nuts and cherries, if desired.

title: lemon surprise
directions: Grate rind and squeeze lemons.
Reserve rind.
Add sugar to juice. Beat at slow speed of electric mixer. Add milk slowly. Beat until smooth. Add reserved rind and lemon extract.
Chill. Pour 2 to 3 tablespoons of syrup into glass. Fill with Seven-Up and serve.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/2 of mushroom soup, beef, onion mix, egg and bread crumbs.
In 12 x 8-inch pan, shape mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Heat remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat to desired consistency.
Spoon over meat loaf.

title: hutzler's cheese bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Knead dough and let rise until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Divide into four parts and put in greased 4 x 8-inch bread pans.
Let rise again and bake in a 300° oven for one hour.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Drain liquid from the peas.
Place peas in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Store in jar in refrigerator and remove garlic bud after one day.
Store up to two weeks in refrigerator.

title: no bake fruit tarts
directions: Cream softened cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Whip heavy cream, adding vanilla to mixture.
Add whipped cream to cream cheese mixture until smooth and blended well.
Spoon mixture into prepared shells.
Top with canned pie filling.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: pop up pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven and drain off excess.
Add the next 8 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle on the Mozzarella cheese, covering evenly.
Mix the milk, oil and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour over hot meat mixture and cheese. Cover completely. Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over the batter. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400° until puffed and golden brown.

title: pork medallions with tangerine and pinenuts
directions: Pound medallions to flatten just slightly.
Season to taste with salt and white pepper.
Heat oil with 1 tablespoon of butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add medallions and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Remove meat to plate and keep warm.
Pour excess fat from pan.
Measure juice and add enough wine to equal 2 cups.
Pour liquid into pork pan over high heat, stirring to loosen the browned bits.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to 1/2 cup.
Whisk in remaining 3 tablespoons of butter, bit by bit.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in tangerine peel, pine nuts and any juice that has collected on plate with pork.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs into whites and yolks.
Add 2 tablespoons milk to egg yolks.
Place remaining milk on stove in a double boiler. Wash the raisins.
Put them in the milk and cook until soft (approximately 15 minutes).
Add rice; cook 5 minutes, then stir in yolks, salt, sugar and spices.
Stir well and cook about 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and pour into serving pan.
Beat whites of eggs lightly, then add sugar.
Spread on top of pudding. Brown lightly in oven.
Serve cold.

title: fennel drop butter wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream until light the butter and sugar. Beat in egg, vanilla, fennel seeds and sifted flour.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into granulated sugar and place unsugared side down on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 7 to 8 minutes or until rims are brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix burger and 1 can pizza sauce and place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer remaining ingredients in order listed and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frisch's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir.
Pour in boiling water gradually.
Let come to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then remove from heat and add butter and jello, stir and let cool.
Fold in strawberries, pour into pie shell and cool. Yields 1 pie.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line baking dish with chipped beef.
Roll boneless chicken breasts with slice of bacon.
Mix 2 cans of mushroom soup,
8 ounces cream cheese, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt to taste.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: hearty chicken noodle soup
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water, chicken and broccoli over medium heat.
Heat through, stirring often.
Serves 2.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix hot rice with frozen broccoli, soups and onion soup mix.
Pour half of mixture into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together soda and buttermilk in a small bowl. Combine oil and sugar. Add bananas, flour, eggs, soda and buttermilk mixture, vanilla and nuts. Stir together. Fill 2 small loaf pans 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cake brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix in cocoa and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 squares.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook noodles and add to hamburger mixture.
Mix Ragu sauce, hamburger, and noodles together.
Using a 9x13-inch pan, put 1/2 the pepperoni in the bottom of the pan. Add hamburger mixture. Place more pepperoni on top.
Add cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: toffee
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar.
Cook until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Then cook without stirring to 290°, hard crack.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Do not overmix.
When slightly cooled, melt semi-sweet chocolate and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread over top, then sprinkle on remainder of nuts.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and meal.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add the three liquids gradually.
Add the lemon rind.
Pour into an unbaked shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tequila sunrise
directions: Put grenadine into 8-ounce glass; fill with ice cubes.
Add tequila.
Fill with orange juice.
Do not stir!

title: philly fudge
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and chill overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt pepper and garlic.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts until crumb-like.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until golden brown (at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool.

title: swirled almond candy
directions: To toast whole almonds, spread nuts in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Toast nuts in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: kick off nachos
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine soup and salsa over low heat; heat through, stirring often.
Serve over tortilla chips. Top with tomato, shredded cheese and olives.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, then mix in sugar, butter, salt and flour.
Add coconut, milk and vanilla.
Brush unbaked crust with melted butter and set by baking few minutes before pouring in filling.
Bake until brown in slow oven at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes.
Enough for 2 chickens.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender. Cook cauliflower and peas together until tender. Pour in buttered baking dish the macaroni and cauliflower after draining. Heat mushroom soup with a little milk to make a smooth sauce. You may want to use 2 cans soup. Put tuna on top of macaroni, peas and cauliflower. Pour soup over all. Stir a little to let the soup down in. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° just to heat through.

title: mountain apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar; blend well. Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts. Mix well and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour hot topping over it.
Let cool.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Mix crackers, pecans and coconut; add to egg white mix.
Pour into pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth into soup in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix in remaining ingredients except almonds.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 40 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with almonds. Serves 4.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: santa fe casserole bake
directions: In a medium skillet, brown meat and stir until crumbly; drain well.
Add taco spices and seasonings; blend well.

In small bowl combine broth and flour add to meat mixture; bring to a boil to slightly thicken liquid; stir in sour cream and chilles blend well. In a 13 inch by 9 inch by 2 inch lightly greased glass baking dish place 1/2 of chips, 1/2 cheese and half of green chillies layer again with remaining ingredients ending with green onions.
Bake uncovered in a 375° oven for 20 minutes let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: country-style oatmeal bread
directions: Add oats and salt to boiling water in saucepan.
Stir in sugar and butter.
Remove from heat.
Set aside until mixture cools between 105° to 115°.
In large mixing bowl, soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add cooled oat mixture.
Gradually stir in flour to make a stiff dough.

title: spinach fandango(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Brown meat, onion and seasonings in large frying pan.
Add frozen spinach.
Cover and cook (checking and stirring now and then) until tender spinach is thawed.
While spinach is thawing, saute mushrooms in butter or margarine until tender-crisp.
Add to spinach mixture and drain well in colander.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream, spinach mixture and grated cheese.
Mix well. Place in 9 x 14-inch baking dish and cover with sliced cheese. Bake at 250° to 300° in conventional oven or on High in microwave until cheese is melted and dish is heated through.
Can be served as a main dish with salad and bread or as a side dish with fish.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box (6 to 7 minutes).
Drain. Beat eggs; add milk, sugar and salt.
Stir.
Pour over drained macaroni in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Be sure all noodles are covered in milk-egg mixture; add more milk if necessary.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Mix the Cool Whip and condensed milk into the vanilla pudding.
Then layer this mixture, the bananas and the vanilla wafers in a large dish.
Top with crumbled wafers or decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add and slightly beat eggs.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift together and stir in alternately with water, flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Do not overbeat. Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into greased regular loaf pan and bake. Turn out on wire rack and cool.
Store in covered tin box or wrap tightly and store in refrigerator.
Loaf will keep nicely several days.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple; add jello.
Mix in buttermilk and Cool Whip. May add nuts if desired.
Chill.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving with chips.

title: easy snack
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Pour spaghetti sauce over heated meat.
Ready to serve with toothpicks.

title: aunt babe's rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions, using bouillon in place of water, set aside.
Drain artichokes slightly and chop.
Slice onions using green part also.
Slice olives and mix artichokes, onions, olive and bell pepper with rice.
Add curry powder to mayonnaise and mix with other ingredients.	Best served at room temperature.

title: cinnamon gelatin mold
directions: Add cinnamon hearts to the boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Cool until slightly thickened.
Add the chilled evaporated milk and beat with mixer or blender until light and fluffy.
(Use a large bowl.)
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Spray a skillet with cooking spray and brown turkey ham. Remove ham.
In skillet, combine eggs, milk, peas and red pepper. Cook and stir over medium heat about 6 minutes. Do not boil. Stir in ham and half of the Parmesan.
Heat through.
Pour over cooked and drained hot pasta.
Toss together.
Sprinkle with black pepper and remaining Parmesan.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomato, onions, olives, beans, cheese, meat and dressing.
Refrigerate.
Top with crushed tortilla chips and toss lightly just before serving.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and water.
Cook in double boiler until slightly thickens.
Put some in beaten egg yolks and then add back to mixture and cook until thickened enough for pie.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Cool and pour into precooked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Cream remaining ingredients.
Layer in a large flower pot (one that has not been used for real plants), starting and ending with Oreo cookie crumbs (about 4 to 5 layers).
Chill. When ready to serve, put in artifical flowers so it looks like a pot of dirt.
Gummy worms give a very realistic effect when set about the flowers.
Spoon out when ready to serve.
Serves 24.

title: mallow-nut squares
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into prepared pan; chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: pasta primavera with a twist
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrots over medium heat; let boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook for 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Add chicken.
Heat through; stir.
Serve over macaroni; toss before serving.

title: chicken breasts with garlic cream
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add garlic. Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring.
Add flour and continue cooking until smooth and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened (5 to 7 minutes).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving marinade; chop artichokes coarsely. In a 2 to 4-cup electric slow cooker, combine artichokes, chiles, mayonnaise and cheese. Cover and heat until cheese is melted. Stir gently to mix ingredients, then blend in 1/2 to 1 tablespoon of the reserved marinade to give mixture a good dipping consistency. Serve hot.

title: e z fruit dip
directions: Blend equal parts of both ingredients by stirring vigorously with a fork until smooth. Excellent with fresh strawberries, tart apples and peaches.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt together over low heat the chocolate and butterscotch chips and the peanut butter.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into a well-greased jelly roll pan and cool completely.
Melt the oleo and add the evaporated milk and the dry pudding mix.
Boil until thick.
Remove from heat and add the powdered sugar and vanilla. Mix well and spread over the first layer.
Cool completely.
Melt the remainder of the first mixture and add the peanuts.
Spread on top of the filling layer.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix well and put in oblong pan.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Pour over the mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: nut tropical cake
directions: Put nuts, dates and mixed candied fruit into large bowl. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nuts and fruit. Mix with hands until nuts and fruit are coated.
Beat eggs until foamy; add vanilla.
Stir into nut-fruit mixture until well mixed. Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 pan.
Spread evenly. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and soda.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Divide into 2 crusts.
Top with filling and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns with cheese, sour cream, soup, butter and onions.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made a day before serving.

title: summer sauce for pasta
directions: Melt butter, add garlic.
Add tomatoes, with juice.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes or so.
Add basil.
Simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
Pour over angel hair pasta and toss with cheese.

title: fritters, apple or corn
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.

title: chicken oven easy
directions: Melt oleo.
Dip chicken pieces in this and place in baking dish.
Crush potato chips in bag and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: black bing cherry salad
directions: Mix jello (use cherry juice and pineapple juice for liquid). When starts to jell, add pineapple and stir.
Cut cherries open and place a piece of cream cheese and 1/2 of a pecan in the middle.
Place in rows in the jello.
(Can also scatter pieces of cream cheese and chopped nuts through the jello.)

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together well and let stand overnight.

title: custard pie with own crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be made with imitation eggs and skim milk. Use a little more of the imitation eggs.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly browned around edges.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Add hot water to jello, mix and cool.
Best when cool and add sugar, rind of lemon and juice of one.
Beat carnation milk until heavy.
Fold jello mixture into milk.
Line dish or pan with cookies crumbs, pour mixture into dish then cover with more cookie crumbs.
Note:
Crush 12 cookies to line pan then 9 more for sprinkling on top.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, milk and drained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oranges, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased cake pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, blend cherry syrup, jelly and cornstarch.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes, or until slightly thickened, stirring 2 times.
Add cherries.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes.
Place brandy in 1 cup measure.
Microwave at High for 30 seconds.
Pour over hot cherry sauce; flame.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: pizza bites
directions: Brown sausage and beef together.
Add cheese and melt.
When mixed well, spread onto party bread.
Serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Heat the tea bags with cold water, pineapple juice, lemon juice and sugar to taste.
Add water and cloves.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine vegetables and tomato sauce in casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake at 350° at least 30 minutes.

title: pudding poke cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Remove from oven.
Immediately poke holes down through cake to pan with round handle of wooden spoon.
(Or poke holes with a plastic drinking straw, using turning motion to make large holes.)
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.

title: never-fail caramel filling
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Let cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat and beat.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until proper consistency to spread.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and take out one oven rack.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff (like meringue).
Fold in nuts and chips.
Place 1 layer of foil on rack, then drop cookies by the teaspoonful onto foil covered rack. Place rack back in the oven.
Turn oven off!
Leave overnight. Do not open oven!!!!!

title: black beans fantastic
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover, then drain and rinse. Put beans in large pot with chicken broth and water enough to cover. Bring to a boil. While beans are heating, saute vegetables in the olive oil until soft. When beans begin to boil, add sauteed vegetables, salt, pepper and ham.
Cook until tender and the liquid has thickened, about 2 1/2 hours on lower heat.
Add vinegar the last 15 minutes of cooking time. Serve hot over rice or at room temperature as a relish.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Into hot cooked spaghetti noodles, stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti noodles into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Cook ground beef and add it to prepared spaghetti sauce and heat through.
Put meat sauce on top of cottage cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour. Add milk and cream. Add broth. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil; reduce heat. Stir in chicken and a dash of pepper. Heat again just to a boil. Serve immediately.
Garnish with snipped parsley and pimento if desired. Serve with warm rolls or breadsticks. Serves 4.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown together ground beef, onion and garlic. Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together. You can also pour over orange sherbet and add ginger ale.

title: turtle pecan cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until creamy.
Add sugar, flour, salt and vanilla; mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in cream.
Pour over crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 200°; continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: rum balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except sugar.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Store in tight container. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix; roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut in about 1-inch squares.
Drop in boiling broth and cook quickly.
Will serve 6 people.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix milk and pudding for 1 minute; let stand for 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and Oreos.
Spoon onto crust.
Freeze for 6 hours.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: blue goose pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; set aside.
Mix together pecans, butter and flour; press out evenly in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread top mixture over crust; then spread blueberry filling over top.

title: pilgrim's punch
directions: Combine cranberry cocktail, orange and lemon juice.
Pour over ice cubes in bowl.
Pour in ginger ale.
Makes two quarts.
Low in sugar.

title: crunchy wheat germ sticks
directions: Combine 3/4 cup wheat germ, flour, chives and salt.
Cut in butter until coarse like meal.
Add egg and 1 tablespoon milk; mix well.
Pinch off dough and shape into 3 1/2-inch long sticks. Brush with 1 tablespoon milk and roll in 1/4 cup wheat germ.
Bake at 425° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: lazy pierogi casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium sized bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and onion salt together.
Spoon over noodles and spread.
Cover with a layer of noodles.

title: dressing
directions: Beat eggs and add all ingredients together.
If not a little soupy, add one cup hot water.
Pour in Pam sprayed pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.
Cut in squares.

title: homemade croutons
directions: On breadboard, use a pastry brush to coat both sides of bread with oil.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan and garlic powder (both sides).
Cut slices into cubes and toast other side until golden brown.
Cool and then store cubes in closed container. Great for Caesar salads or even as a snack.

title: orange cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients well.
Add baking powder and soda (dissolved in a small amount of water).
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix and heat soup with gelatin.
(Do not boil.)

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and pack into a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: paw paw glaze's shrimp and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion, celery, garlic, bell pepper and parsley until tender in melted butter.
Combine in large casserole dish the rice, vegetables, tomatoes, soup and raw shrimp.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour, or until rice is tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and bananas; beat well. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture with milk and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon pieces.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: tiramisu
directions: Combine condensed milk, dream whip, and cream; mix with hand mixer until it thickens.
Mix the warm milk with coffee and then let it cool.
Dip the graham crackers in the milk/coffee mixture. Then spread a layer of the condensed milk mixture on the crackers. Using the same method, continue making 3 or 4 more layers.
End with a layer of the condensed milk mixture.
Sprinkle top with cocoa powder.

title: seafarer sandwich
directions: Put fish in a food chopper, then combine with the rest of ingredients.
Spread this mix on a piece of French bread.
Top with sliced tomato, 2 strips bacon (cooked) and top with Swiss cheese slices.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.
Spread makes enough for 6 sandwiches.

title: ginger's spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and store in an airtight container.
To prepare tea, place 1 or 2 teaspoons of the mix in a cup or mug and add boiling water.
Stir and serve.

title: country style steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and dredge in seasoned flour. Melt 1/4 cup margarine in large frying pan; add onions and mushrooms.
Cook until onions are tender and mushrooms are lightly browned.
Remove onions and mushrooms from pan; set aside.
Add remaining 1/4 cup margarine; when melted, add the steak and brown on both sides.
Stir in rest of ingredients along with mushroom mixture.
Cover and cook until meat is tender enough to cut with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix Crisco oil, dill, garlic salt and dressing.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Mix well and let set at least 1 hour.

title: broken glass dessert
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar and margarine to make crust. Reserve half of crust mixture and place remainder in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Dissolve each package of gelatin (lemon, lime and strawberry) separately in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Chill each until firm, then cut into squares.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Heat pineapple juice and sugar together; cool and add to unflavored gelatin.
Add the whipped cream.
Add cut up gelatin squares and mix.
Pour gelatin mixture into pan on top of graham cracker crust and top with remaining graham cracker crust mixture. Chill until serving time.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Combine boiling water, dates and soda; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Gradually add this to the creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and the chopped nuts.
Combine mixture with date mixture, mixing well.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, milk and butter.
Boil 3 minutes.
Spread over each layer and sprinkle coconut over.
Cover and let sit until cool.
This is a delicious moist cake.
It is hard to believe you can get 3 layers with only 1 1/2 cups of flour but you can.
(Just don't eat the whole thing.)

title: homemade noodles
directions: Drop eggs into bowl with flour and pinch of salt.
Mix, using fingers.
Add cold water and knead.
Let rest 30 minutes.
Using 1/4 of dough, roll out and let dry for 30 minutes.
Cut into desired strips.
Repeat.
Cook in boiling water.

title: one-dish chicken shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in a 10-inch saute pan; add onion and saute until soft.
Remove from the heat and add chicken, sour cream, thyme, sage, salt, drained mushrooms and 1/2 cup of the grated cheese.
Set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients together in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter. Add boiling water to cover.
Add salt and bay leaf.
Boil vegetables until potatoes are tender.
Place in blender.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Thin soup with milk.
Add salt, paprika and dash of Worcestershire.
When ready to serve, garnish with parsley, chives, cut up franks or diced ham or croutons.
Serve hot or cold.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs, sour cream and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg together and mix with creamed ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle topping on top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Deep fry pork until brown 10 minutes.
Saute onion, bamboo shoot, pineapple, carrot, mushroom and pepper.
Cook sauce ingredients over low heat until thick.
Add pork and sauce to vegetables; serve hot with rice.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Can be frozen after it sets.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Cook onion in half of margarine.
Let cook and add poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and mustard in saucepan.
Slit rolls and brush mixture on rolls.
Add ham and cheese on rolls.
Place rolls back in foil pans, cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Brush margarine on top of rolls just after removing biscuits from oven.

title: spicy chicken bites
directions: Combine lemon juice, water, rosemary, garlic, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce in small bowl.
Stir in chicken cubes, cover and chill 24 hours.

title: turkey or chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain. Combine soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese melts and sauce is hot. Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas and carrots and pimento.
Spoon into a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch or larger baking dish.
Combine crumbs and Parmesan cheese and sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 30 minutes or until hot.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars; beat just until combined. Stir in chocolate chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Place cream cheese mixture on a large piece of plastic wrap; shape into a ball. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat when mixture reaches soft-ball stage.
Add vanilla and beat for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits and fold over.
Place nuts in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Top with biscuits, then with cinnamon.
Mix together and boil the brown sugar, water and margarine, placing over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well, then add cocoa, salt, soda, flour and cold water.
Fills a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple and zucchini salad
directions: Combine oil and next 6 ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Combine apples and next 3 ingredients; toss with dressing.
Yield:
8 - 10 servings.
Serve on leaf lettuce.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Whip cottage cheese until creamy.
Add Cool Whip and stir in jello (do not add water to jello) and fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: biscuit mix (refrigerate)
directions: Blend with fork or blender.

title: winter carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon over carrots.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of carrots.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Whip eggs slightly.
Then add sugar, flour, lemon juice and rind.
Pour on top of base and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool slightly and sprinkle with plenty of confectioners sugar.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: In a large bowl, mix soup, sour cream, chili peppers, onion and olives. Mix together and add Jack cheese. Remove 2 cups of this mixture and set aside. Add chicken to remainder. Drop large spoonfuls of chicken mixture into tortillas, enchilada style, and roll. Place into 13 x 9 glass pan. Pour remainder of mixture over chalupas to cover. Top with all the Cheddar and spread to cover. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until hot and bubbly. Enjoy.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie crust.
Bake slow.
Makes 2 pies.

title: three cheese ball
directions: Leave cheese at room temperature for about 2 hours.
Mix all ingredients (except nuts) with mixer until ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape in a ball and roll in chopped nuts. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cook noodles ahead of time.
Cook sausage and onions until meat is brown and onions are done.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and chili powder.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add noodles and stir in sour cream.
Heat to serving temperature and serve.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together into a bowl.
Stir in milk and melted margarine.
Spread into a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Pour over entire batter the hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar.
Let cool.
Mix all together.
Add 1/4 cup oil.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Separate roll dough into 4 rectangles; seal perforations. Place 8 slices pepperoni on each rectangle.
Sprinkle with cheese. Roll up each rectangle from narrow side to enclose filling; seal edges.
Cut each roll into 4 slices.
Pinch dough together on 1 side of each slice to seal.
Place sealed side down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Heat pizza sauce and serve with pinwheels.

title: aunt judy's cinnamon ornaments
directions: Put water in tea kettle or pan on stove on high heat.
When surface is covered with bouncing, breaking bubbles, you have your boiling water.
This is good to add to any jello for dessert and also makes a good drink when poured over a small amount of instant tea or coffee in a cup.

title: microwave marshmallow crispy bars
directions: Microwave butter in a 9-inch square baking dish on High for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in marshmallows and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed, stirring after the first minute.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal, 1/3 at a time, stirring with a fork until well coated.
Press into dish.
Cool.
Cut into 36 even bars.

title: old south lime pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in water and lime mixture for 12 hours or overnight (do not use aluminum ware).
Remove cucumbers from mixture and rinse 3 times in fresh cold water.
Soak 3 hours in ice water.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and mixed pickling spices in large pot.
Bring to a low boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Remove syrup from heat and add cucumbers and soak for 5 to 6 hours.
Boil slices in syrup 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine ground beef, egg, bread, parsley, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well.
Shape in loaf and place in baking dish.
Add beef broth.
Bake uncovered 1 hour, basting frequently.
Remove from oven and cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Slice thinly and serve with Dijon mustard.
Delicious when heated, but I think it is at its best when chilled (thinly sliced and served with mustard).

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer until onions are tender. Serve warm over spinach salad.

title: orange-pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients together in freezer container of ice cream maker and fill to line according to manufacturer's instructions. Freeze according to instructions using ice and ice cream rock salt.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Place raw meat in roaster.
Place onion and celery on top of meat.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour over meat. Cover and roast at 350° until beef is very tender or lower heat and slow roast all day.
Remove fat and bone. Shred meat with a fork while still hot.
Return to sauce.
Leftover freezes well.

title: tammy murray's etouffee
directions: Saute veggies in butter.
When clear, add tomato sauce.
Cook until condensed to a paste, about 20 to 30 minutes, then add crawfish, soup, green onion and parsley.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add Tony's to taste.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand; roll into balls.
Press down with a sugared fork.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Rinse and drain several times. Put beans in a large pot and add 6 quarts water, bell pepper, onions, thyme, parsley, bacon grease, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring these ingredients to boil, then add one bag of crab boil.
(Note:
Do not break open bag of crab boil.) Add Tabasco and ketchup.
Cover pot and boil slowly until beans are done.
When done, remove bag.
Don't break bag.
One hour before serving, cut smoked sausage into small round pieces and brown in skillet.
Add to beans.
Cook rice.
Heat beans and sausage until good and hot.
Serve over rice.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Mix gelatin according to directions on package using juice from pineapple as part of the cold water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Let set and serve.
Very good with casseroles or just as a snack.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken parts and place in shallow dish and cover with buttermilk. Let sit 3-4 hours or overnight (overnight is best). Drain. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Dredge in flour. Deep fry. ENJOY!!!!

title: hot dip(serves 15 to 20)
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with water biscuits.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter, and margarine together in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and mix well, stirring into and coating cereal.
Put powdered sugar in bag, add cereal mixture and shake well.
Cool and store in airtight containers.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Do not mix!
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexicali salad
directions: Combine black beans, garbanzo beans, corn, onion, red bell pepper, green bell pepper, tomato, dressing, chiles and honey in medium glass or ceramic bowl; refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pioneer day cookies
directions: In large bowl mix sugar, oleo and Crisco until fluffy.
In small bowl mix egg, Pet milk, vanilla, baking soda and dash of salt.
Add flour to sugar mixture along with mixture in small bowl. Roll into small balls.
Flatten with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Must dip glass in sugar after each press.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes (light golden color).

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk; add to mixture.
Cream together.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Chill for two hours.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Remove meat from bones.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix soups and milk in bowl; pour over chicken.
Add peas, drained.
Pour dressing over top.
Melt butter and pour over dressing.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Use large pan and put in sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and add Certo.
Bring to a boil, cool and add maple syrup flavoring.

title: pepper pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir in pecans and let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Spread pecans in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: avon cookies
directions: Mix together as for pie crust.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat together for at least 1 minute eggs, sugar, lemon juice and flour.
Will be thin. Pour on top of baked crust and bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. (A cup of coconut may be sprinkled on top of the custard and baked with it.)
Cut into small squares.

title: crock pot pizza
directions: Cook noodles per pkg directions.
Brown meat and drain.
Add chopped onion, pepper, pepperoni, mushrooms, spaghetti and pizza sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; slice into 1/3-inch slices.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet; brush slices with oil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Layer half eggplant and tomatoes in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with half cracker crumbs and half of cheese.
Repeat layers using remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: creole sausage and rice bake
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain and set aside.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones and cut in small pieces.
Saute chopped onion in melted margarine (1/2 stick) until onion becomes clear.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Mix brown sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in maple flavoring.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: french sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or just scrub and rinse.
Cut into thin slices not all the way through.
Put potatoes into baking dish and fan out slices.
Sprinkle with salt and butter and herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese again.
Bake for additional 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: dawn's dip
directions: Cream all together until smooth.
Great with vegetables!

title: cranberry-strawberry jam
directions: Put the ingredients listed in a pot and bring to a boil, stirring so it doesn't burn.
Continue cooking on a medium heat for 5 full minutes.
Pour into 2 jars.
Ready when cold.

title: johnny's famous apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix ingredients in the order given. Pour ingredients into greased 10 x 14 pan. Bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: poppy chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and soup.
Add stock, then top with crushed Ritz crackers or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top before baking.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain, debone and flake salmon.
Add all ingredients; mix well by hand.
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Form into 8 or 12 patties as desired.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: snowy cheese salad
directions: Pour water over gelatin and dissolve.
Add mustard, paprika, salt and food coloring.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in celery, onion and green pepper.
Combine cottage cheese, whipped cream and sour cream.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Brush bottom and sides of crust with egg.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheet until light brown.
Combine apples, lemon juice, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, salt and spices; spoon onto crust.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over filling.
Bake for about 50 minutes.

title: scrumptious sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Put on sheet pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, milk, oats and seasonings.
Blend thoroughly. Add ground beef.
Mix lightly but well.
Pack in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Grate the Cheddar cheese.
Mix the cheese, sausage and Bisquick together.
Roll into balls a little smaller than a walnut.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. This makes approximately 100 balls. They freeze well or you can cut recipe in half.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and vanilla.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°).
Add vanilla.
Beat until it begins to thicken.
Add nuts.
Stir until well coated.
Turn onto greased cookie sheet.
Separate into individual pieces.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Set aside.
In a
small bowl beat egg yolks;
mix in sweetened condensed milk.
Gradually
add
lime peel and juice.
Stir to combine well.
Fold
mixture into egg whites.
Add food coloring. Pour into crust.
Freeze
for 3 hours.
Let stand for 15 minutes at
room
temperature
before
serving.
Serve
with whipped topping.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Pour in the hot water and stir well.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast and eggs and then flour, one cup at a time. Refrigerate for at least two hours.
Take out and shape rolls, letting rise 2 hours before baking in a 450° oven for about 12 minutes.

title: s'more bars
directions: Blend together flour, oats, butter, brown sugar, salt, soda and milk until crumbly.
Press into bottom of greased pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Add dressing, refrigerate until cool.
Add Miracle Whip.
Add all other ingredients (celery, raisins, zucchini and cucumber are optional, according to preference).
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Serves 15.
Makes a meal by itself.
Serve with hot bread, if desired.

title: peanut butter cocoa cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar, add milk and butter.
Heat in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats to chocolate mixture.
Stir thoroughly and spoon out on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat the oil in a large heavy iron pot over medium heat, then stir in the flour and make a roux; this should take about 45 minutes.
To the roux, add the onions, bell pepper, parsley and green onions, stirring after each addition.
Cook, stirring frequently, until the vegetables are tender, then slowly add 1 cup of the stock, stirring until it forms a thick paste.
Stir in the garlic, wine and the remaining stock, then add Worcestershire, salt, hot sauce and stir.
Bring to a boil, then add the crawfish, shrimp and crabs.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice with file.
Leftovers can be frozen in smaller portions.
Yields 6 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry salad or dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 or 15 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic hot fruit casserole
directions: Put applesauce on bottom of 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish to cover 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add layer of peach slices.
Dot with butter and sprinkle again with cinnamon.
Do the same with the pears and pineapple.
Top with bread or rusk crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in oven in large Pyrex or Corning Ware dish.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 cup self-rising flour in mixing bowl and mix well.
Add 1 cup milk to mixture, mix well and pour over melted butter.
Pour 1 large can sliced sweetened peaches (juices and all) over this.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream and Cool Whip.

title: indian fried bread
directions: Mix flour and milk together to resemble pancake texture. Melt butter in skillet; pour batter in hot skillet in approximately 2 to 3-inch circles.
After little holes appear on bread, flip over on other side; fry until done.
Spread with peanut butter and eat.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend carrots with sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add this to carrot mixture; mix well. Stir in nuts.

title: creamy taco
directions: Brown meat on low to medium heat; drain.
Blend together the beans, chili mix and tomatoes.
Pour into ground meat.
Add the can of milk and slowly add the cut up cheese.
Cook until smooth. Serve over Fritos.

title: easy pulled b.b.q.  pork
directions: Combine garlic, seasoning salt, pepper and cayenne pepper; rub into roast. Place roast in large Dutch oven and fill half way with water. Add onion. Bring to a rolling boil over high heat. Reduce heat, simmer and let cook until meat falls off the bone (approximately 3 to 4 hours depending on size of roast). Place hot roast in a serving bowl and pour on your favorite BBQ sauce. Stir until well blended. Serve!

title: oyster dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with Melba rounds.
Makes a lot.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well, gradually add flour and nutmeg to creamed mixture.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together all wet ingredients except zucchini and carrots. Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and carrots.
Add nuts.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Cooking time:
325° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and cumin.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture. Fry chicken until golden.
Remove.
Saute onion, garlic and sweet potato in same pan.
Stir 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Add broth, salsa and oregano.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add zucchini, corn and hot sauce and cook until chicken is done. Serve with Cornbread (recipe follows).

title: classic quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook onion (sliced thin) in reserved drippings until tender; drain.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into cookie sheet.
Add a layer of frozen hash browns.
Add sausage.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over sausage.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.
Shake Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli and all ingredients. Pour in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Dot with butter.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl. Add milk and melted butter; stir until smooth.
Spread batter over bottom of buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle berries over batter.
Combine water, sugar and remaining butter in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over berries.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: hominy and cheese casserole
directions: Heat soup, chilies, onions and cheese over low heat until cheese melts.
Drain hominy and put into casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over hominy.
Cover; bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: brownie bites
directions: Melt margarine and add sugars, flour, cocoa and egg substitute.
Blend well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan that has been sprayed with vegetable oil. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in
large
bowl.
Add
eggs and oil and stir until moist
(do not beat).
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Bake
in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Turn into serving dish. Cool in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese and Cool Whip get room temperature.
Blend all ingredients (except crust) in a mixer until creamy.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In large skillet, heat oil, then stir-fry rice and onions. Add soy sauce and seasoning mix and stir-fry for a few minutes. Push rice to outside of pan, leaving a circle, then add eggs and scramble within the circle.

title: mimi's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and chop eggplant; add salt and onion.
Cook 20 minutes using only enough water to get eggplant steaming.
Drain and mash slightly.
Add cheese (use only sharp cheddar), milk, egg and tomatoes.
Place in a sightly greased casserole dish and top with either cornbread or crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in the remaining ingredients except walnuts.
Chill slightly; form into a ball. Chill well.
Press the walnuts over ball.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter in large frying pan. Add mushroom soup, string beans and cheese.
Mix until cheese melts.
Place in casserole and top with onion rings.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Cream together cream cheese, yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Butter or Pam spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pan with 1 package rolls, then spread the filling over.
Place remaining package of rolls on top and sprinkle the top with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil for 7 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take off heat.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Stir together until chips are melted.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper quickly before it hardens or pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: lime pie
directions: Bake pie shell in oven preheated at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove and set aside to cool.
Place milk, egg yolks, lime rind and juice in stainless steel bowl.
Set over saucepan half-filled with hot water on medium-low heat.
Cook mixture until thickened, stirring constantly.
Transfer bowl to counter and let cool.
Fold in egg whites, then whipped cream, mixing with spatula.
Pour filling into a pie shell and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish pie with toasted almonds or slices of lime if desired.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats.
Mix together and drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: baked stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 (8 or 9-inch) round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frigo lasagna
directions: Blend all ingredients, except Frigo Mozzarella cheese and Parma Zest and lasagna noodles, to a smooth consistency.

title: no-fail caramel frosting
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil; boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add baking soda and vanilla.
Beat until stiff enough to spread.
(Beat well.) Yield:
Frosting for three 8-inch layers.

title: more
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add onions, green peppers and celery.
Cook over low heat for several minutes. Add cooked noodles, tomato sauce, corn,
chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Combine hominy, tamales, sausage and soup mix.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. If desired, garnish top with additional tamales. Sprinkle cheese atop.
Return to oven to melt cheese and heat tamale garnish.
Serves 6.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Boil the potatoes and onion in a large pot in the water.
When tender (do not drain), mash briefly with potato masher, then add salmon, milk and creamed corn.
Heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste and serve with whole grain rolls or cornbread and fruit for a healthy, quick, winter supper.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt cheese, butter and cocoa. Beat in half of the sugar, then vanilla, then rest of sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Chill, then cut into small squares.

title: southern style chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Leave skin on.
Cook about 80 minutes until tender.
Cook in about three times as much water as you have chicken.
When chicken is tender, remove from broth and set aside, covered.
Season to suit taste with salt and pepper. Mix 1 cup flour with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Add to broth to make it thick.
Mix 1 cup flour with 1 cup milk.
Add salt.
Dip a teaspoon into thickened broth, then get a spoonful of batter and drop into broth.
Do not stir.
Continue dropping spoonfuls of batter into broth until all is used.
Cover and let cook 10 minutes.
Take a spoon and very gently turn dumplings over. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
When finished, gently drop chicken pieces back into pot.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: In a double boiler, melt the chocolate chips.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Dip strawberries in halfway.
Cool on wax paper on a cookie sheet.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, water and cocoa.
Cool.
Add flour, salt, sugar, eggs, soda and sour cream.
Mix well.
(Batter will be very thin.)
Bake in 8 x 12 x 1-inch pan for 20 minutes at 375°.
Frost while warm.

title: must try turnip gravy
directions: In a large skillet, put enough oil to fry meat.
Flour and season meat; fry in oil until brown but not done.
While this is cooking, chop all vegetables.
Slowly to meat, add flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, until all oil is absorbed.
To this, add vegetable mixture, turning.
Cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables wilt.
Add cold water to cover meat and vegetables, plus 2 inches over.
Add seasonings to taste.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; add onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add broth and bring to boil.
Add broccoli, Tabasco and pepper.
Bring to a boil again, then simmer until broccoli is tender.

title: amish chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Melt butter and cook mushrooms until tender.
Blend in flour; add broth, milk, salt and pepper and stir until thick.
Put into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole with chicken and noodles.
Put cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onions and simmer.
Then add chili powder and stir well.
Add the tomato sauce and 4 cans water.
Add 1/4 pound crackers for thickness.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and sprinkle in the flour.
When flour turns brown, add in the half-and-half, stirring slowly. Simmer, stirring regularly for 5 minutes.
Add the chiles, onion, and cayenne and simmer 10 minutes.
In a medium bowl mix most of the cheese (saving some for the top) and onion.
Heat oil in skillet and dip each tortilla into hot oil for 5 seconds; drain on paper towel.
Scoop cheese mixture on each tortilla, roll up and place in a 9-inch by 13-inch baking pan.
Top with green chile sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° until heated through and bubbly.
Garnish with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Put all ingredients in a heavy pan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until dough cleans sides of pan.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and knead until pliable.
Store in an airtight container.

title: ham and cream cheese balls
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add the onions, ham and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Adjust garlic powder, if necessary, by tasting mixture.
Chill well.
Form into 2 or 3 balls and roll in shredded Cheddar to coat.
Walnuts may also be used to coat.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Spray 6 squares of aluminum foil with cooking spray.
Place open bun on foil and spread with Pizza Quick. Divide sausage and spread on 6 buns.
Put other desired toppings on top of sausage.
Place cheese on top and close the bun.
Roll in foil and bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: christmas banquet salad(serves 20)
directions: Dissolve 1 package lime jello in 1 cup hot water in double boiler.
Add marshmallows and stir over hot water until marshmallows are almost dissolved.
Let cool and add pineapple. Blend mayonnaise and softened cream cheese and add to lime mixture.
Refrigerate until thick, stirring occasionally.
Fold in topping and pecans.
Pour in oblong pan.
Refrigerate until firm. While this is setting, mix cherry or strawberry jello in 1 3/4 cups of hot water.
Let cool until thickened.
Pour over lime mixture and let set overnight.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes enough for 6 people.

title: endive or celery with dijon sauce(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine endives or celery and onion with water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Transfer to 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Reserve liquid and add water to make 1/2 cup.
Set aside.
Stir together sour cream, mustard, flour, sugar, bouillon granules and pepper.
Stir in reserved liquid.
Spoon sauce over vegetables.
Chill until ready to bake.

title: mexican tamale pie
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in hot fat until just tender.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 300° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cube 2 slices of bread; place in a greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a medium size bowl; spoon over cubed bread.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat eggs lightly with milk in a small bowl; pour over chicken and bread.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Spoon soup evenly over bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and mix by hand.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Pour into clean hot pint jars and seal.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, chill and serve.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine thawed lemonade and orange juice concentrates with the rest of ingredients.
Taste.
Add sugar is necessary.
Serve with ice ring in punch bowl.
This will serve about 25 punch cups.
If cups are small, it will serve 30.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Put ingredients together and bake in tightly covered pan in 250° oven for 5 hours.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package.
Saute onions in butter until brown.
Add cheese to mashed potatoes, along with 1/2 of onions and butter.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir hamburger in Dutch oven until light brown. Drain; stir in remaining ingredients.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: uncle don's favorite upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange drained pineapple slices over sugar; reserve liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes and turn upside down.
Serve warm with ice cream, whipped cream or alone. Excellent during pheasant hunting season.

title: oatmeal cookie
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg. Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Add oatmeal, raisins and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for exactly 8 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: paper-bag pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour into deep-dish pie shell. Cover with second crust.
Moisten edges with water before placing top one on.
Crimp edges to seal.
Cut slits for steam to escape. Sprinkle sugar/cinnamon mixture on top crust. Place pie in paper bag.
Fold and staple end shut.
Bake 1 hour at 375°. Open after cooling.
Serves 6.

title: maple walnut squash puree
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook squash for 25 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Puree in blender, or by hand, until smooth.
Blend in maple syrup, butter, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Spoon into shallow, greased 8-cup casserole or baking dish.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes.
Serve immediately garnished with walnuts.

title: peanut butter and butterfinger cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar, beating well.
Add egg whites, beating well.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Set aside.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture; mix well.
Stir in candy.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: heavenly delights
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar and flavorings, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour. Beat well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Shape into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar again.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: linda's lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add Prego and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, cheeses, parsley and pepper.

title: tom and harrys(makes 8 servings)
directions: In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, combine eggnog and nectar.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.
Do not boil. Stir in rum and brandy.
Heat through.
Ladle Tom and Harrys into mugs. Top with dollops of whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 6 to 8 (6 ounce) servings.

title: french cherry dessert
directions: Whip Dream Whip and fold into sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over crust and top with filling.
