Chill at least 8 hours.

title: rice pilaf(sweet, good and easy)
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onions until limp.
Add rice and cook 1 minute.
Pour in stock, add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and
turn
to
simmer
and cover with lid.
Simmer 23 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix well first 4 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Best if chilled several hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Soak tortillas in chicken broth and line casserole dish with them.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add chicken, onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix soups and chili powder together.
Spread over other ingredients.
Pour Ro-Tel over that, then sprinkle more cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a bundt pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Bring water, sugar and butter to a boil.
Put in dry milk in a blender or pour the mixture over dry milk and blend for 1 minute, until thick.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 pan. Mix coconut and chopped pecans and sprinkle in bottom of pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed and spread over coconut and pecans. Mix together the powdered sugar, cream cheese and oleo. Drop by spoonfuls on batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: fiesta shrimp salad
directions: Arrange lettuce leaves	on
plates.	Place 2 avocado slices on either side
of	plate.	Place
fruit, shrimp, onion rings
and pecans in
a
bowl.
Toss
with
dressing.	Arrange salad on plates between avocado slices.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon coconut over each serving.
Serves
generously for lunch or as part of a soup and salad supper.

title: becky's chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse well under cold running water.
Drain chicken well and flake.
Add to macaroni with the onion and Salad Supreme.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Taste and add additional Salad Supreme, if desired.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the rest, except nuts.
If using electric mixer, stir in nuts by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly with hands.
Shape into balls.
Chill overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Cut thin round steak into strips; season.
Put a piece of bacon and onion on each strip.
Roll up and close with a round toothpick.
Brown, then cook on low heat for about 45 minutes.

title: martha's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and cook for twenty minutes slowly.
Brush on chops, chicken or ribs.
Cook on grill or in oven.
Wonderful.

title: cabbage with apples
directions: Slice apple.
Shred cabbage.
Place apples and cabbage in pan with vinegars, wine and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer on low for 30 minutes.
When done, remove bay leaf.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: alta's popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt and corn syrup to 300° to 325° to hard ball stage.
Add vinegar and vanilla; cook to light or crack stage (270°).
Pour over popcorn; lightly mold into balls.

title: pinch me buns
directions: Thaw frozen bread for 3 to 4 hours.
Heat Karo, brown sugar, milk, butter and cinnamon on top of stove.
Then pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Sprinkle in nuts.
Pinch small pieces of bread and drop into the pan.
Let it rise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cook onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk and broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, rice and any remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered,
at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add Crisco oil, flour and whipping cream alternately.
Add flavoring.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325°for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar; pour into pie shell, then layer with the bananas.
Top with whipped cream. Layer top with strawberries and nuts.
Let chill in refrigerator for a couple of hours, then slice and serve.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar
and eggs together, then flour, baking powder and vanilla; beat
well.
Heat	butter and milk over low heat. Melt butter well; then add the rest of the ingredients slowly. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt
butter;
add other ingredients, stirring over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to full rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat.

title: toffee fudge
directions: Mix the brown sugar, Marshmallow Creme, milk and margarine; boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in candy and butterscotch chips until melted.
Pour in a 9-inch greased pan.
Chill.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.	Bake at 325° until firm.
For a variety, add 1/4 cup chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Measure sugar, milk, salt and butter in large kettle.
Cook on medium heat with a candy thermometer to 235° (soft boil stage). Take off stove.
Put in vanilla and peanut butter and stir until it starts to get thick.
Pour out in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (buttered or use Pam).
Let cool.
Cut while still a little warm.

title: barbecue hamburg
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper and then saute in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add hamburg.
When hamburg is browned, then add 1/2 bottle ketchup or chili sauce, 3 tablespoons green relish, brown sugar and vinegar.
Let simmer with cover on for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Five minutes before finished, sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm croutons and finish baking.

title: thanksgiving rolls
directions: Dissolve salt, yeast, water and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Melt butter and add to yeast mixture. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add 3/4 cup sugar and flour; mix well.
Let rise to double. Roll 1/4-inch and cut out. Put in pan and brush with melted butter. Let rise to double again. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger and minced onions in skillet; add tomatoes, chili con carne and taco spice mix and cook 10 minutes.
Add olives.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, adding the creme de menthe. Cool completely!
Spread jar of fudge topping over cooled cake. Over fudge spread Cool Whip to which 3 tablespoons of creme de menthe has been added.
Refrigerate.
Flavor improves if left in refrigerator for 10 to 12 hours before serving.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones (reserve 1/2 cup broth). Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Combine soups, milk and broth. Heat thoroughly.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange, cranberry sauce and pecans.
Chill in mold until firm.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Cook penne according to package directions; drain. Add chicken, mushroom soup, Ro-Tel, 1 cup shredded Cheddar and cayenne pepper. Spoon into 9 x 13 baking pan. Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.

title: black punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine squash, macaroni and cheese.
Combine egg, milk and margarine.
Stir mixture and top with crushed soda crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot spice tea (or russian tea)
directions: Combine
water,
tea
bags, cloves and cinnamon sticks; bring to
a boil, then simmer for awhile.
Remove tea bags and spices. Add
sugar
and juices.
Delicious and cozy on a cold evening!

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together white sugar, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon with apples.
Put into pastry lined pie pan.
Top with butter and top crust.
Seal and slit top a little.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 425° oven.

title: sunday morning biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in the Crisco.
Into a measuring cup, break the egg and beat with a fork.
Add enough milk or cream to make 3/4 cup.
Add the milk and egg to the dry ingredients.
Mix until all liquid is taken up. (Do not handle too much.)

title: veal stew
directions: Saute veal in oil 10 minutes.
While water is releasing from veal, add garlic and continue sauteing.
Fifteen minutes later, add peeled tomatoes (crushed with fork), peas, salt, pepper and water to cover.
Cook 15 minutes (high).
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
As water reduces continue adding water to consistency of your choice.
Serve over buttered rice.
Serves 4.

title: oxtail gumbo
directions: Brown oxtail in margarine on all sides in Dutch oven.
Add water, 1/4 cup celery, 1/2 cup onion, parsley, salt, chili powder, paprika, thyme, garlic and crushed red pepper.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Chill; remove fat and strain broth.
Remove meat from bones. Combine undrained tomatoes, okra, 1 cup celery, 1/2 cup onion, meat, broth and sugar in a large saucepan; cover and simmer 45 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: egg pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour; add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop vegetables in 1/2 inch pieces (may want onions slightly smaller). Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight Can be used as a salad or vegetable dish.

title: american chez slice "cheese"
directions: Blend the first 2 ingredients.
Add boiling water and blend more.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: hazelnut oatmeal pancakes
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes. Whisk in eggs.
Mix in flour, sugar, baking soda and salt; stir in chopped hazelnuts.
Heat griddle with slight film of vegetable oil until hot.
Ladle small amount of batter, cooking until top of cake breaks bubbles; flip and cook other side until golden.
Serve with melted butter and hot maple syrup, fruit or yogurt.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Combine soup mix and rice in baking pan.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Heat soup and 1 soup can water in saucepan.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Yields 6 servings.

title: honey muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except baking soda, together.
Put 1 teaspoon baking soda in cup; fill with boiling water and stir into first mixture.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water together; set aside.
Melt butter; add buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture to lukewarm liquid.
Add salt, sugar, soda and beaten egg.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Beat all together and add 2 cups flour.
Put dough in greased bowl and leave in a cool placed until 2 hours prior to serving.
Roll out and cut.
Grease tops and bottoms with butter; fold in half. Place in pans and let rise at room temperature.
Bake at 450° about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: soupa guadalajara
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes. In a 5-quart kettle, heat oil over medium heat; add meat and brown well.
Push to sides and add onion and garlic.
Stir in chile powder, oregano, cumin, water, broth and beans.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cover and refrigerate.
Skim fat from broth.
Heat broth to boiling.
Add carrots.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in corn and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with condiments: sour cream, sliced green onions, lemon/lime wedges, jalapeno sauce and cherry tomatoes.

title: french fried cauliflower au gratin
directions: Remove large outer leaves of cauliflower.
Break into flowerets.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling water (salted) for 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Combine eggs and water; beat well.

title: pizza burger sandwiches
directions: Grill or fry burgers (use 1/3 pound patties or smaller; larger ones are hard to handle); season them to your personal taste. Do not overcook.

title: "lemon blossom pie"
directions: Stir together yolks, lemon juice and peeling, set aside.
In a saucepan mix sugar, cornstarch and salt, gradually stir in boiling water.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring briskly. Continue to stir and let boil until clear and smoothly thickened (about 3 minutes).
Carefully stir in eggs and lemon mixture and boil, stirring, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Cool 5 minutes, then pour into baked pie shell.
Now ready for the meringue.

title: greek chocolate balls
directions: Put nuts, chocolate and zwieback through food chopper.
Chop fine.
Add cinnamon, 1 1/2 tablespoons confectioners sugar and rose water.
Form into 36 small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Pour over layers of sausage and cheese. Add a little extra milk, if needed, to cover sausage.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until egg is set.

title: easy brownie pizza
directions: Grease and flour 12 x 1/2-inch pizza pan (or two 9-inch layer cake pans).
In 3-quart saucepan bring corn syrup and heavy cream to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Set aside 2/3 cup of the chocolate sauce.
Add butter and sugar to remaining sauce; stir until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until firm.
Cool on rack.
Top with ice cream, fruit, nuts and chocolate sauce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients while broccoli is cooking.
Then mix in broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry sorbet
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Place berries, water, 1/2 cup of the sugar, the lemon juice and liqueur in a 5 cup blender container.
Blend until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Pour strawberry mixture through a strainer into an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Freeze until firm 3 to 4 hours.

title: crustless coconut and pecan pie
directions: Spray 2 (8 7/8-inch or 9 x 2-inch) foil pans with "Pam" cooking spray.
Put eggs, butter and milk in large mixer bowl and beat well.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Add the flavoring and mix well.
Take out beaters and add coconut and pecans.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread coconut on and follow with a layer of each chip.
Finish layers with walnuts.
Sprinkle milk over pan evenly.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate before cutting.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise.
Wash and drain crab meat.
Add to all other ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chicken salad sandwich spread
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on slice of bread or spoon into pita pocket along with shredded lettuce and tomato slices.
Makes enough filling for 4 sandwiches.
Contains 100 calories each.

title: ten layer salad
directions: Arrange first 6 ingredients in layers in 13 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle with sugar, then Parmesan cheese and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Top with bacon and cover with plastic wrap.
Make 24 hours ahead of time and refrigerate until served.
I also like to add a layer of fresh sliced mushrooms.
Or make it a main dish by adding a layer of ham strips.

title: cherry torte
directions: Whip milk and Dream Whip together until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of crust and spread.
Top with pie filling; chill about 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon; stir in apples.
Turn into pastry shell.
Combine remaining flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are done.
If pie browns too quickly, cover edge with aluminum foil.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix together your favorite tuna salad.
Cut the top off of the tomatoes and a thin piece off the bottom.
Scoop out the seeds and turn tomatoes over to drain.
Stuff the tomatoes with your tuna salad.
Break the cheese in pieces and cover the top.
Slice olives in 1/2 and in center of the cheese make a hole and put olive in. Place tomatoes on a microwave dish.
Microwave until cheese melts. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swedish cucumber salad
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and parsley in a bowl.
Add water, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: philly cheese wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended. Add rest of ingredients.
Chill.
Place drinks glass in center of plate, spoon mixture around glass.
Remove glass and garnish with parsley and pimento.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients (except chicken wings).
Mix well.
Marinate wings for 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Bake for 15 minutes, then broil to crisp.

title: night before mashed potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes. Whip hot potatoes with cream cheese and sour cream. Beat until fluffy and smooth. Add salt and pepper. Place in a buttered 9 x 13 in. baking dish. Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with seasoned salt. Cover with foil and refrigerate, Potatoes can be frozen at this point and thawed before baking. Bake, covered with foil, at 325° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix
margarine	and
cheese
by
hand.	Add flour, Rice Krispies
and cayenne pepper.
Make into walnut size balls and press with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and reduce heat. Bake until slightly brown.	Makes 48 to 50 wafers.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash peeled and seeded avocados in taco sauce; add remaining ingredients, minced very fine.
Mix and serve on lettuce.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and eggs.
Heat milk to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup milk and add to mixture.
Add 1 pint milk and mix well.
Let dough rise to double in bulk which is about 3 hours.
Keep dough in warm place.
Knead and let rise for another hour.

title: million pie
directions: Blend lemon juice into condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and refrigerate overnight or 3 hours before serving.
Yields enough for 2 baked pie shells.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix together will be dry put in a 9 x 13 baking dish and pat down.
Do not grease pan.

title: popover
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat ingredients to make a smooth batter.
Add melted butter and continue beating for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased custard cups or muffin pans. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Lower temperature to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and soda together.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead well.
It may be necessary to knead in more flour.
Cut out biscuits and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for a week.
Makes 24 to 30 biscuits.

title: company corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Beat egg well.
Grate the cheese and add to egg.
Pour in 3/4 can of milk.
Mash pimento and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Cook over slow fire, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Pour into small bowl and allow to cool.
Cover with clear wrap to refrigerate.

title: garlic chicken pizza
directions: Generously spread olive oil over top of Boboli bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Spread fresh garlic from garlic press or Polaner chopped garlic on olive oil. Precook chicken breasts and cut into bite-sized pieces. Spread over crust. Top with mushrooms, onions, cheese, garlic salt and oregano. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: low-fat key lime pie
directions: Mix a little more than half of Cool Whip with Condensed Milk. Add Key Lime Juice.
Pour into cracker crust.
Refrigerate for several hours until set.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top just before serving.
Garnish with Lime Twists.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Roll out crust to approximately 13 x 9-inch.
Down center of dough place corned beef, Swiss cheese, sauerkraut and salad dressing.
Cut sides of dough and crisscross over mixture.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with caraway seed. If using bread dough, let rise approximately 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: veal scallopine marsala
directions: Dredge veal cutlets in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add garlic.
Add veal.
Brown quickly, then remove veal to baking pan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to skillet and brown mushrooms.
Add Marsala cooking wine and boil 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over veal.
Cover and bake approximately 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: In medium bowl, using a fork toss bread crumbs with milk, egg, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add ground chuck and mix well.
Shape lightly into balls.
In large pan melt 1 1/2 Tbsp. butter, saute meatballs turning until brown all over.
Remove meatballs and add the rest of the
butter and onion, saute about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in bouillon and bring to a boil, stirring; reduce heat.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile cook beans as directed on package, drain well.
Add beans and sour cream to meatballs, stirring to combine.
Reheat gently about 5 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at a mild speed for 2 minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
For an oblong pan or layer pans, 30 to 35 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Decorate with your favorite frosting.

title: carolina trifle
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
In trifle bowl make a layer of Cool Whip.
Then make a layer of pudding then layer of broken up cookies.
Repeat layers ending with Cool Whip on top.
Garnish top with cookies.

title: creamless celery potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil until hot.
Add celery, potatoes, onions and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender (about 6 minutes).
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together first five ingredients.
Mix last four ingredients together, add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in moderate oven, 350°, about 30 minutes.
Ice with your favorite chocolate or vanilla icing.

title: peaches and cream cheese dessert
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.
Combine in a large bowl the first 7 ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Place the peaches or pineapple over the batter.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each
ingredient
in large bowl (saving bacon for top).

title: cure all
directions: Shake together and store covered in refrigerator.

title: creamy fruit dessert
directions: Stir peaches, pineapple, strawberries, kiwi fruit, brown sugar and spices in a medium bowl.
Layer fruit alternately with whipped topping in large dessert or trifle bowl.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Mash bananas and add lemon juice.
Cream shortening-sugar mixture and beat until light and fluffy.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk. Beat after each addition.
Fold in banana mixture.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cover leaves with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Place mixture in leaves and roll.
Put rolls in baking or casserole dish.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven and add sauce to the top of rolls.
Cover and cook for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease large casserole.
Sprinkle half of the stuffing on the bottom.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: cranberry banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and cranberries.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: in a hurry banana pudding
directions: Prepare mix as directed on package for pudding.
Line bottom and sides of 10 x 6-inch baking dish with wafers.
Layer half of bananas, half of pudding and 1 cup marshmallows in baking dish; cover with additional wafers.
Top with remaining bananas, pudding and marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until marshmallows are golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: russian paskha
directions: Put cheese through sieve into a large bowl.
Mix eggs and sugar together in another bowl and then add to the cheese and mix. Place in a pan
on the stove and heat, stirring constantly until the first bubbles appear.
Take off the stove and allow to cool. Do not place in refrigerator.
Line a clean, clay flowerpot with a double layer of cheesecloth after rinsing it with cold water. Pour in the cheese mixture.
Fold over the ends of the cheesecloth, put a plate and weight of some kind, to force mixture to drain into a bowl placed below.
Store in fridge for 1 1/2 days.
Remove from pot and remove the cloth and enjoy eating it.

title: fried eggplant
directions: After slicing eggplant, lay out on paper towel and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 30 to 40 minutes.
Dry off, dip in beaten eggs and then seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry in Wesson oil until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve.

title: zucchini sausage casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water 10 minutes.
Scoop out insides of shells and mash.
Drain shells and place on baking sheet.
Remove sausage meat from casings; break it up and saute 5 minutes.
Stir in onion and garlic; saute until onion is soft. Stir in zucchini and crumbs.
Spoon into shells; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook the cake mix according to directions on box.
Mix the coconut, milk and pineapple.
Put on cake while it is hot.
Let cool, then top with Cool Whip and shredded coconut (frozen kind). Leave off Cool Whip, if you wish.

title: virgin margarita
directions: Chop mix and ice for 1 minute in blender.
Add strawberries and chop for 20 seconds or until thoroughly blended.
Wet glass rim and dip in salt (optional).
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 8 people.

title: buttermilk pies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in a large unbaked pie shell or 2 small shells at 325° until firm.

title: hot fudge frosting
directions: Melt oleo, cocoa and
milk in saucepan.
Remove and add sugar. Blend well.
Add vanilla.	Pour over hot cake.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix together pudding, milk
and
sugar.
Add
Cool Whip and mix well.
Spray bottom of
x
13-inch
pan
with
Pam. Layer a thin layer of graham
cracker
crumbs.
Then
put
1/2 mixture of pudding on top of crumbs.
Layer more graham crumbs and then add rest of
pudding mixture.
Add chocolate frosting over this (hint: if you microwave the frosting for 60 seconds it will pour perfectly).

title: fix-n-mix bread
directions: In Fix-N-Mix (Tupperware) bowl, put 9 cups of flour.
Make a well in the center and put in scalded milk, water, sugar, eggs, salt and 2 packages dry yeast.
Do not mix.
Seal the bowl and burp it.
Store in warm place until the seal pops (15 to 20 minutes). Melt 1 cup of butter or margarine, pour over the flour mixture and knead a little bit, leaving very sticky.
Seal and burp the bowl. Store in warm place until the seal pops (20 to 30 minutes).
Makes 4 loaves of bread or 1 loaf and four pans of rolls.
Rise again, then bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil.
Add the eggs.
Stir in flour, soda, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Make into little balls and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy do fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in large, heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Stir about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in bowl until well blended.
Add chopped eggs and chicken.
Toss lightly until combined.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
When ready to serve, fill lettuce cup and sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Saute onion and meat until brown.
Cut tops and remove seeds from peppers; par-boil until slightly soft, about 2 minutes. Remove from water and set aside to cool.
Cook and drain rice.
Mix meat, rice and cheese together.
Season to taste.
Stuff peppers and place in large pot.
Pour on tomato juice and cook at low temperature for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Can also be baked in large Pyrex dish at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(Cover with foil until almost done and remove for last few minutes.)

title: mound bars
directions: Mix filling and refrigerate until cold.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: silver star sandwich
directions: Toast an English muffin. Pile the ingredients on muffin.
Add Durkee mustard.
Enjoy.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Mix rice, corn, garlic, green onion, milk, chili powder, red pepper seasoning, salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Arrange tomato slices on top, overlapping slightly. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese during the final 5 minutes of cooking.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate lovers' delight
directions: Crush cookies on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Layer pudding on top of cookies.
Layer Cool Whip on top pudding.
May sprinkle top layer with chocolate sprinkles for decoration.

title: slim dip
directions: Put in blender until well mixed.
Chill and serve with vegetables or chips.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 2 quart bowl or 8 cup Pyrex measuring cup.
Cook on full power for 5 minutes.
Stir and cook for 2 more minutes.
Add butter and cook 1 to 1-1/2 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla and stir until light and fluffy. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix together, then beat 1 egg white until stiff and add to above mixture.
Dip fish in batter and fry.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk 4 minutes.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.

title: chicken and swiss cheese
directions: Boil boneless chicken breasts.
Place chicken in pan.
Pour soup over it.
Place cheese slices on top.
Sprinkle crumbled toast over top, then pour melted butter on top.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Blend cheese and pineapple. Add dates, cherries, lemon juice and salt. Fold in whipped cream and nuts. Pour into a quart mold and freeze until firm!

title: quick mashed potatoes with cheese
directions: Fix potatoes
according
to the microwave instructions; add the minced onion
to
the water and margarine before cooking. When you
have
potatoes
ready,
sprinkle
with cheese, bacon and the green
onion tops.
Return to microwave and cook on High for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and dice.
Place half of bread in ungreased 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard and pimento.
Put crab meat in bowl.
Add salt and pepper; gently toss with mayonnaise mixture, taking care not to break pieces.
Spread over bread; top with remaining bread.
Beat eggs; mix with milk. Pour over crab meat and bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours prior to baking.

title: prize peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with 1 cup sugar. Slowly stir in vanilla to make batter.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, combine milk, margarine, salt and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Add yeast mixture, then 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 cups flour.
Mix well until dough is firm. Grease bowl.
Place dough in bowl and let rise to double in size in warm place out of draft.
Make into loaves or place in one pound coffee can that has been well oiled.
Can should only be half full.
Let rise until dough puffs to top of can.
Brush top with margarine.
Bake at 375° until brown. Removes easier if allowed to cool slightly.

title: baked spinach stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops
off
tomatoes
and about 1/3 of the way down; gently scoop
out
pulp, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Drain tomatoes.
Melt butter in a skillet. Add mushrooms and saute until tender.
Stir in spinach, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cook and stir
for
2 minutes.
Remove
from heat.
Blend eggs and bread
crumbs together
and
stir into spinach mixture.
Salt tomato
shells, fill with filling.
Stand filled tomatoes in a greased 10
x
6 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 25
minutes.
If desired, sprinkle tops with buttered crumbs. Serve hot.

title: traditional sage stuffing(thanksgiving)
directions: Dry bread in a very slow oven (250°); place in a large bowl. Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add to bread with salt, pepper and sage. Beat eggs lightly in a small bowl; stir into stuffing.
Add enough of the chicken broth to make a moist mixture.
Stuff turkey cavity lightly.
Spoon any extra stuffing into a buttered casserole dish. Spoon a little extra chicken broth over top and bake, uncovered, with turkey during the last half hour of roasting.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: dropped tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; add sugar.
Beat well with electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and lemon flavor. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 6 dozen.

title: purple cow
directions: Put grape juice, sugar and milk in jar and shake well. Add 1/2 cup chilled ginger ale and 1 large serving of vanilla ice cream. Stir with spoon until blended. Pour in large cold glass; add extra ginger ale to fill glass 3/4 full. Top with another serving of ice cream. Makes 1 serving.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix for about 5 minutes on low speed.
Bake in greased tube pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: jello cake(delightful summer dessert)
directions: Mix ingredients in mixer.
Add lemon extract and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.
Time may vary 5 to 15 minutes, depending on oven.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In a medium bowl beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Put in pie shell.

title: chocolate mix
directions: Put 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture to a large coffee cup.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter and chocolate chips in microwave. Put cereal in large bowl and pour melted mixture over cereal. Stir to coat.
Put powdered sugar in brown grocery bag and then pour cereal mixture in bag.
Shake to coat.
Pour in bowl and enjoy.

title: chicken don't peek
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, place rice, top with chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add water and celery soup; cover tightly with foil and seal well.
Bake at 325° or 2 to 3 hours.
Don't peek, so the rice will cook.
During the last few minutes, remove foil to allow the meat to brown.

title: creamy sauce
directions: Add butter to beaten egg slowly. Add powdered sugar, mixing well. Blend in whipping cream and vanilla. Serve over pound cake.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread slices of boiled ham with softened cream cheese. (You can
add
your favorite herbs with the cream cheese, dill or crushed
drained
pineapple
are great.) Roll slices up and slice in bite size pieces.

title: chicken pilaff
directions: Chop celery and onion.
Brown in butter or margarine.
Add raw rice to the vegetable mixture.
Saute rice until slightly browned. Add three cups hot water in which 2 or 3 chicken bouillon cubes have been dissolved.
Place rice mixture in oven for 1/2 hour, then layer skinned chicken breasts or a whole cut up chicken over rice and bake for 20 more minutes.
Check chicken to see that it is cooked thoroughly.
(If chicken is not cooked, be sure to check that the rice is not getting too dry.
Add extra water if necessary.)
You may wish to spoon sour cream or yogurt over rice before serving.

title: sausage corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut sausage into quarters lengthwise Then cut across into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: wine jelly
directions: Measure sugar and wine into top of double boiler and mix well. Place over rapid boiling water and stir until sugar is completely dissolved, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and all at once stir in fruit pectin.
Mix well; skim off foam if necessary.
Pour quickly into hot, scalded jars; fill within 1/8-inch from top. Cover at once with hot paraffin.
Makes 4 cups.

title: aunt mary's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs, oats, pecans and raisins.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Roll dough into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Put on greased sheet and smash down with glass cup.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef in a skillet; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar to beef.
Place each biscuit in a greased muffin pan, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown round steak and simmer until the meat is tender; add onions, green peppers, salt, pepper and soy sauce with the sugar and then thicken with cornstarch mixture.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine all vegetables in large bowl. Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water. Let stand for 4 hours then drain thoroughly. Put vegetables in a colander and press out all excess liquid. Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Stir in drained vegetables. simmer for 10 minutes. Pour in jars and seal.

title: breakfast tortillas
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Melt margarine in skillet. Pour egg mixture into pan and cook, stirring until eggs become firm.
Spread eggs in the center of each tortillas.
Top with cheese and salsa.
Fold or roll tortilla and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Score one side of the steak by making shallow cuts in a crisscross pattern.
Place meat in a shallow dish or plastic bag. Combine soy sauce, oil, vinegar, sugar and ginger; pour over meat. Cover and refrigerate for 1 to 3 days or at room temperature for up to 3 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and broil or grill for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Slice thinly at an angle across the grain.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and spice.
Combine milk, pumpkin, oil and slightly beaten egg.
Stir into dry ingredients until blended. Mix with a fork.
Fill paper muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mrs. johnson's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in cooking oil until tender. Rinse ketchup bottle with water.
Combine with sauteed mixture and simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: meat-za pizza
directions: Mix together with a fork the ground beef, garlic salt, bread or cracker crumbs and milk.
Pat out in a layer over the pan and 1/2 inch up the sides.
Spread the catsup, tomato paste or tomato soup over the meat.
Spread a layer of mushroom pieces over the previous layer.
Lay on the slices of cheese, cut into strips. Sprinkle with oregano.
If desired, sprinkle on Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: nancy's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13 pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat cream cheese and butter until soft and smooth.
Add vanilla, sugar, cornstarch; beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time to batter and reduce speed to low.
Add cream while beating, scraping bowl as necessary.
Beat in lemon juice.
Pour batter into pan.
Place pan in larger pan and pour in hot water to 1-inch. Bake 30 minutes, then turn pans.
Increase heat to 375° and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Remove cake pan from hot water and place on rack.
Let stand until bottom of cake pan is completely cool.
Refrigerate.
Sometimes a 9 x 13 pan is too small for this recipe.
You may need to use a deeper or larger one.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour 1/2 gallon milk into a pot and heat it on the stove.
When the milk is warm, put the rice and sugar and cook until thick. Beat eggs in separate bowl and add vanilla.
Then remove rice from stove for about 1 minute (to stop cooking), then add beaten eggs and fold until mixed together.
Pour into bowl until cool and then put cinnamon all over the top (if you wish).

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Unmold and slice.

title: meatless chili
directions: Heat oil in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion and pepper and cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring often, until onion is translucent. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors. Makes 8 cups or 4 servings.
Contains only 5 g. fat per serving as listed.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in a baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, eggs and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chips, vanilla and pecans.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eclair pie
directions: Mix enough graham cracker crust mix to cover the bottom of a medium to large casserole dish.
In another bowl, mix milk and pudding; add to Cool Whip.
Quickly pour on top of graham cracker crust.
Smooth out evenly.
Next, remove top of frosting mix and heat in microwave for 20 seconds or more (just enough to make it pourable).
Quickly pour and spread over pudding before the frosting sets.
Chill and serve.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; add meat.
Cook until no longer red.
Stir occasionally.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Peel and slice eggplant.
Combine eggs and 1 tablespoon of water.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip eggplant slices in egg mixture, then crumb mixture.
Coat well.
Fry in 1 tablespoon of hot olive oil until brown.
Drain.
Arrange eggplant and Parmesan cheese in layers.
Top with Mozzarella slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake, uncovered, 25 minutes.

title: spicy cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage; cut up pepper and onion.
Put everything in stock pot or a large pot.
Add spices.
Put half water and 1/2 can of beer.
Add bacon and grease last.
Add minced garlic in with spices.
Cook slow until tender enough for your taste.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (or larger).
Mix rhubarb with sugar well.
Top cake mix with rhubarb, evenly.
Pour whipping cream over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apple pizza
directions: Spread pie crust onto a pizza pan.
Use both crusts on one pan.
Peel and slice apples and place on crust.
Mix and sprinkle cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg on apples.
Mix flour, sugar and oleo with fingers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast-brunch casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns; blot dry with paper towel.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put potatoes in pan.
Pour oleo on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: mock duck soup
directions: Cook spareribs covered with water until it boils.
Spill this water out; rinse ribs and start again the same way, adding the onion, prunes and rest of ingredients except flour and vinegar. Cook until meat is tender.
Strain soup.
Put broth aside.
Put all except meat through a sieve.
Put pulp back in broth.
Mix flour, sour cream and vinegar in blender, then add to broth (while cooking).
Cook to near boil.
Serve with noodles.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken; top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over the cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted into chicken with ease.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley to serve.
Makes 4 servings.
(Add 15 to 20 minutes for bone-in chicken.)

title: fudge cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for a few minutes.
Then add quick oats, peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Cool.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased pan.

title: sugar-free carrot cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Heat raisins, pineapple and juices.
Boil 2 minutes.
Puree raisin mixture in blender.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk, vanilla and bananas.
Blend. Add to dry ingredients and stir.
Add carrots, nuts and coconut. Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in 13 x 9-inch sprayed pan.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In a deep bowl layer:
crumbled brownies, chocolate mousse, Heath chips and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: strawberries to die for
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Serve with fresh strawberries.
Perfect for dipping.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix carrots, pepper and onions together in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onion with water. Boil until soft.
Mix the flour with the milk.
Add the milk, cheese, butter and chopped parsley to potatoes and heat until very hot but not boiling. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crockpot macaroni & cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 7 minutes, drain.
Mix all ingredients except 3 cups cheese into large crock pot.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook on low for 4 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix lightly with mayonnaise. Chill thoroughly and serve.

title: padre island sand dollars
directions: Beat together butter and powdered sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Gradually mix in flour.
Stir in vanilla and salt and mix well.
Using level tablespoons of dough, shape into balls.
Press one side of each ball into granulated sugar.
Place sugar side up on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies can be placed close together because they do not spread when cooking.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes or until done, but not browned.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with jello.
Put into a 4-cup jello mold or bowl. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil to deep fry.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute chopped onions in a little olive oil.
Add tomato paste and whole tomatoes.
Add several cups water, then add seasonings: salt, pepper, lots of sweet basil and parsley and not as much oregano.
Add wine.
Simmer for several hours or until the right consistency is reached.
If meat sauce is desired, add browned ground beef or cooked meat balls and cook for another 1/2 hour or so.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Immediately press a chocolate Kiss in the center of each cookie.
Remove to wire rack and cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper together.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Put everything in bowl except walnuts.
Put in microwave for 2 or 3 minutes until melted.
Stir good; add nuts.
Pour into a square pan that's been sprayed with Pam.
Chill until set.
You can use white chocolate chips, too, instead of milk chocolate chips.
This fudge is very easy to make and so, so, so creamy.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine all ingredients except cheese and chow mein noodles.
Put in prepared dish and top with cheese and noodles.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Blend together; form into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan; mix well.
Crumble about 2 cups corn flakes over top; drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: deviled seafood
directions: Mix all except bread crumbs and margarine.
Mound in individual seafood shells or spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Combine bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with lemon slices and sprigs of parsley.

title: broccoli soup #1
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add broccoli and bouillon cubes.
Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Serve and enjoy.

title: bob hall's soon to be famous spicy crab and clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes a bit first.
Mix in a large bowl and microwave on High for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring when you think of it.
Salt to taste if needed.

title: roasted garlic broccoli
directions: Combine ingredients in a terra cotta baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Broccoli should be served while still firm.

title: elegant seafood pasta with dill dressing
directions: Steam lobster, shrimp and crab.
(Add Old Bay seasoning and a slice of lemon to water, if desired.) Remove from shells and chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together well and beat with mixer.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. May also be rolled in dried parsley or paprika.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel zucchini, remove large seeds, dice and cook.
Drain off liquid if not cooked up.
Mash, it's okay if lumpy.

title: denver sandwiches for one
directions: In small bowl, combine egg, ham, milk, onion powder and basil. Beat well.
Melt margarine in small skillet over medium heat.
Add bell pepper.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes or until crisp and tender. Reduce heat to low . Add egg mixture to skillet.
Cook until set, but still moist, stirring occasionally.
Place tomato slice on each muffin half, top with egg mixture.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: For icing, mix sour cream, coconut and sugar and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: meat balls
directions: Using your hands, mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls about the size of a ping-pong ball or smaller.
Brown in an iron skillet with several tablespoons of cooking oil.
Drain.
Add the meat balls to the spaghetti sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 12 minutes or more.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: kraut salad
directions: Cook 1 cup
sugar
and
1/2 cup vinegar for 10 minutes, then pour over listed ingredients and chill.

title: lennie's chicken and rice
directions: In a rectangular casserole dish mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place enough raw chicken pieces over rice to cover casserole dish.
Place pats of butter over chicken.
Seal casserole dish with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until rice absorbs liquid.

title: hot fudge ice cream sauce
directions: Melt chips
and
butter
in
large saucepan over low to medium heat,
stirring
constantly.
Gradually
add sugar and milk. Blend
well.
Increase heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly for
minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and salt. Serve warm.
Store sauce in refrigerator.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Cream all ingredients until smooth. Chill.
Serve with cut up fresh fruit.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat in 2 eggs.
Sift together next 3 ingredients; add to sugar and butter.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Refrigerate dough for 4 hours or overnight.
Roll into small balls, about marble size.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with glass bottom dipped in sugar each time (dip glass in sugar each time so won't stick to dough).
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Season and flour steak and brown in butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in broth and simmer about 1 hour or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook for 5 minutes and serve over noodles.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken for at least 1 hour, then shred.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, Rotel and 1/2 can of the chicken broth together and heat on low or until hot.
Best to use a 12x9x3 pan. Then put a layer of chicken, layer of onions, layer of grated cheese and a layer of crushed Doritos.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blackened seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients, then stir in 1 stick melted butter before covering meat or fish.

title: coconut cake squares
directions: Mix and bake according to directions in 9 x 13 pan.

title: rosy strawberry ring
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add berries; stir until thickened and thawed.
Stir in pineapple, bananas and lemon juice.
Pour into a 6 1/2-cup mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill until firm, 5 to 6 hours.
Serve with Sour Cream Dressing.

title: deviled pecans
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add pecans and toss to coat.
Spread on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.
Stir every 8 minutes or so.
Drain on paper towels. Serve at room temperature, but store in fridge if you have any left!

title: ginger ale mint cooler
directions: Combine water, sugar and mint in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and strain mint; discard leaves and chill.
To serve, combine chilled mint mixture, lemon juice and ginger ale.
Stir well. Pour over crushed ice or regular ice cubes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You can boil potatoes or bake them.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until well done, or knife or toothpick comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, blend first 8 ingredients until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl frequently.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Scrape sides of bowl occasionally.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork in a straight or crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets immediately.
Yields about 60 cookies.

title: pineapple smoothie
directions: In blender, put approximately 1 c milk. Add 3 to 4 scoops ice cream. You can use chocolate, vanilla, or swirl. Add in about 1/4 c hershey's chocolate syrup. Blend.

title: aunt lee's cheese grits
directions: Add salt
to water.
Bring to boil and add grits.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove
from heat and add the next 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs
until
frothy and fold into grits.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Fill casserole half full.

title: mock champagne
directions: Just before serving, mix juice and 7-Up.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chocolates on low heat; do not boil.
Pour in peanuts. Mix until well covered.
Spoon by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes; stir until thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice cubes. Using wire whip, blend in Cool Whip and whip until smooth.
Stir in fruit.
Chill 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped beef.
Chill before serving.

title: outdoor baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and wrap in heavy-duty aluminum foil. Bake on the barbecue grill until potatoes are tender.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine garlic, tomatoes, cuke, green pepper, bread and vinegar in blender until smooth.
Strain mixture through sieve; toss solids out.
Add tomato juice, water, oil, salt and pepper to liquid.
Chill well.
Garnish with croutons.

title: cool chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, orange sections, pineapple and walnuts in large bowl.
Blend oil, orange juice, vinegar and salt. Add to chicken and fruit.
Chill 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise; toss gently and serve.

title: company rice
directions: Melt margarine and add rest of ingredients.
Cover; bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove lid, stir and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare mushrooms, chopped.
Mix chopped stems with cheese, bread crumbs, onions, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano. Stuff mixture in mushroom caps.
Pour oil in baking pan.
Arrange mushrooms.
Pour remaining oil over mushrooms.
Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peach fuzz
directions: Put in blender the peach, lemonade and vodka or rum.
Add ice. Blend until ice is fine.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: "instant" mexican cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Use 3 tsp. mix per cup.

title: salami hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with soup mix.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of this filling mixture on slice of salami.
Cover with slice of salami.
Repeat process 2 to 3 times.
Wrap tightly in wax paper and chill.
Cut into wedges (12 to 16).

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix ingredients all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot crab sandwich
directions: Add salt, lemon juice and pepper to crab; set aside.
Remove crust of bread; butter one side.
Place 6 slices, butter side down, in baking dish.
On each slice place a slice of cheese, a portion of crab and another slice of cheese.
Top with slice of bread, buttered side up.
Pour mixture of beaten eggs, cream and sherry over bread.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Preheat oven to 325°; bake 1 hour.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Begin by preparing the sauce.
Dice the garlic and onion. Saute the onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons olive oil until translucent.
Add the crushed tomatoes and salt; simmer for 30 to 45 minutes. Peel and slice the eggplants.
The slices should be 1/8-inch thick.
Beat the eggs in a wide bowl, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Dip each slice of eggplant in the egg mixture, then dredge in breadcrumbs to coat each side.
Heat 1 cup olive oil in a large frying pan; fry each slice of eggplant until golden, being careful not to overcook.
Drain the fried slices on paper towels.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Mix before serving. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy rhubarb crumble
directions: Layer the ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Place rhubarb on the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle dry jello over rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over jello.
Sprinkle cake mix (yellow or white) over sugar.
Pour water over all ingredients.
Bake in oven for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate iced brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Cream together oleo and sugar. Add eggs until creamy. Add chocolate, vanilla and flour. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Hand mix eggs, sugar, oil, water and pumpkin; add dry ingredients and mix very well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
(Usually done in 1 hour so keep a check on it.)

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar and press firmly into molds.
Unmold immediately.

title: easy pickles
directions: Combine and mix well.
Wash cucumbers and pack whole in a gallon jar.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers.
Finish filling jars with water.
Seal and let set for 2 months.

title: homemade chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until done; separate chicken from broth and set aside to cool.
Add all ingredients except flour to broth and cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove bone from chicken and break chicken into small pieces.
Add to mixture.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to cold water and stir until smooth.
Add to chicken stew. Cook until thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook until tender.
Cool, peel and grate with a coarse grater.
Combine sour cream, cheese, onions, milk and seasoning.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Smooth over with spatula.

title: hot cherry pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Combine and heat cherries, juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve hot with cream.
Serves 6.

title: hot bacon dressing for salad
directions: Place bacon in a large, deep skillet; cook over medium heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble and set aside.

title: vanilla cream cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and water with eggbeater until light.
Slowly add sugar and continue beating.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to yolk mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and salt. Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans that have been greased and floured. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in frying pan.
Drain off grease. Boil potatoes until soft but firm.
Mix cream soup, egg and a little milk.
Layer potatoes, hamburger and cheese in baking dish. Pour soup mixture over them.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cranberry sauce in 2 cups boiling water. Let cool until it can be refrigerated.
Refrigerate until it begins to gel.
Remove and fold in the sour cream and pecans. Place back in refrigerator and let fully gel.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown chuck and onion.
Add mushrooms and remaining ingredients in order given.
Stir thoroughly and simmer.
Cover for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: carciofi ripieni(stuffed artichokes)
directions: Remove outer leaves and cut off artichoke stems. Cover with cold water in deep pan.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: dewey's mexican corn bread with meat
directions: Mix the corn meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt and corn together and set aside.
Saute the beef in bacon drippings.
Drain on paper towel.
Prepare and set aside the onion, grated cheese and jalapeno peppers.

title: brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Mix fruit and nuts.
Add flour and mix with hands.
Add slightly beaten eggs with vanilla; mix well. Grease pans, put in wax or brown paper and grease again.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours or until done.
Cool, remove paper and wrap. May be wrapped in brandy cloth if desired.

title: calico mold
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir over low heat to dissolve gelatin; set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine all other ingredients. Gradually stir in gelatin.
Refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes, until mixture mounds.
Stir well.
Spoon into a 4-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Unmold by dipping in hot water and inverting on platter.
Surround by chips and crackers.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish and cover with lid.
Bake about 1/2 hour or until all liquid is out.
Bake at 300° to 350°.
Cook until rice is done.

title: flank steak
directions: Combine soy sauce and wine in a shallow dish.
Marinate steak for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.
For medium-rare, broil steak 5 minutes on each side, basting once with marinade. Let rest for a few minutes before slicing in thin slices.
Cut across the grain.
Always salt steak after it is cooked to avoid toughening.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: egg yolk doughnuts
directions: Gradually stir sugar into egg yolks.
Add melted butter; beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Dissolve soda and cream of tartar in milk.
Add to mixture.
Combine and add flour, nutmeg, baking powder and salt.
Drop from doughnut maker into hot fat (370° to 380°).
Turn once.
Drain over fryer, then on paper towels. They do not absorb fat.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Makes 48 cups.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: In Dutch oven, prepare fettucini according to package directions; drain.
Remove pan from heat.
In same pan, combine hot fettucini and butter; toss to coat.
Add 1/2 of the cream; toss well.
Add 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese; toss well.
Add remaining cream; toss well to coat.
Add remaining Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg; toss well until coated and creamy.
Serve immediately with pepper and Parmesan cheese. Serves 4.

title: wmpia
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Saute garlic and onion.
Stir in ground beef and seasonings.
Brown well.
Fold in vegetables.
Cook until half done.
Strain in colander and cool.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons of filling in center of wrapper.
Fold edge of wrappers over filling.
Wrap like envelope.
Moisten edge with water to hold it together.
Heat oil to 375°.
Fry until lightly browned.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix
in order given and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: norwegian soup
directions: Combine yellow split peas, ham hocks, onion (chopped fine), chopped thyme and water in large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer until tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, rutabaga, celery root, 1 1/2 cups chopped leek and salt. Return to simmer and cook, covered, stirring occasionally, 30 or 40 minutes more, until vegetables are very tender.
Remove ham hocks; discard skin and bones.
Chop ham fine and return to soup. Sprinkle chopped fresh parsley over top.

title: minnesota bars
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil (be careful not to scorch).
Mix in peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Pour this mixture over Special K cereal which has been placed in a large bowl.
Mix together and pat it firmly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with frosting and cut into squares.

title: blueberry sky pie
directions: Thaw pie crust; prick with fork and divide 1 cup chopped nuts into pie crust.
Bake crust until brown; set aside to cool.
In mixer, put softened cream cheese; add confectioners sugar and mix good.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla flavoring.
Put filling into crust and divide 1 can pie filling over each pie and refrigerate. You can use your favorite pie filling.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Between 2 pieces of waxed paper pound chicken breasts until thin (be careful not to tear holes in them).
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place thin slice of ham and cheese in chicken. Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Let rest in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Roll in beaten egg and water.
Mix cracker crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper and parmesan cheese.
Roll breasts in mixture and let rest again another 20 minutes.
If desired, re-roll in crumb mixture and let rest again.

title: snack oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix until not greasy.

title: joyce's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Cream Crisco and sugar together. Add flour and yeast to mixture, alternating each to sugar and Crisco. Cover and let rise 1 hour. Knead for 3 minutes. Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut out like biscuits. Fold over. Put small piece of butter in each one. Let rise 2 hours. Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 400°.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring to boil; when mixture drop put in water forms a small ball, remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Pour over unsalted popcorn; shape into balls.

title: banana pumpkin bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, margarine and eggs. Beat at medium speed, until
mixture is light and fluffy (1 to 2 minutes).
(Mixture will have curdled appearance.) Add remaining ingredients (except nuts).
Mix just until moist (1 minute); stir in nuts.
Spread into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and add 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 1/2 stick butter. Spread potato mixture in a 9 x 13 baking pan. In a saucepan, cook the white sugar, milk and cornstarch until pudding consistency. Add vanilla to the white sauce. Pour white sauce over the potatoes. Melt 1 stick butter and add oatmeal and remaining cinnamon and brown sugar. Crumble oatmeal mixture over white sauce and bake in a 325° oven until topping is browned slightly.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Blend
flour, salt and lard.
Then blend egg, water and vinegar well and pour over first mixture.
Mix.
Then roll out pie crusts.
Keeps
well
in
refrigerator for several days or freezes well too.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all together and blend well.
Frost cool cake.

title: clara's casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Brown ground beef in same skillet, added to onion and green pepper mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Place in cupcake liners for crust.
Press down.
Beat cream cheese, eggs and 3/4 cup sugar until creamy.
Pour on top of crusts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool a little bit.
Beat sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Spread some on each cream cheese cupcake.
Bake an additional 10 minutes at 375°.
Chill.
Top with canned cherries or blueberry pie filling.

title: water chestnuts hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut bacon strips in halves and wrap around chestnuts, securing with wooden toothpicks.
Place in glass dish and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Drain off grease.
Mix ketchup and sugar together and pour over bacon wrapped chestnuts.
Bake at 300° an additional 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy weiners
directions: In crock-pot pour chili sauce and jam.
Stir, then add little wieners and simmer on low.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix All-Bran, Raisin Bran, sugar and water. Stir well. Add all of the buttermilk and soda.
Mix well.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Bake 20 minutes in a 400° oven. Can be stored in refrigerator for 5 to 6 weeks.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, with a few spoons of flour between eggs, beating after each addition. Stir in remaining dry ingredients and vanilla. Add apples, nuts and coconut; mix well. Grease and flour a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Let set in pan 10 to 15 minutes before turning out.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix sugars and soy in a large bowl.
Place chicken wings in a large casserole dish.
Pour contents of bowl on wings.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Turn wings. Bake 30 minutes more. Turn and bake 20 minutes
more.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Heat oil to 400°.
Mix 1 tablespoon of oil and ingredients with fork.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes until golden.

title: cheese broccoli dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler; once cheese is melted, add the broccoli and soup.
Mix well; serve in crock-pot with chips (corn or Tostitos chips).

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger. Add brown sugar and mix well. With pastry blender, cut in butter and shortening. Mix molasses and vinegar and gradually stir into mixture.
Mix thoroughly with hands if necessary. Wrap in waxed paper or plastic and chill several hours until firm enough to roll.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve red hots and Jell-O in hot water.
Place in refrigerator until partially set.
When partially set, add applesauce and celery.
Return to refrigerator until set.
Serve.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry salt pork until well done. Add onions and cook until transparent, about 4 to 5 minutes. Add potatoes and water. Continue cooking until potatoes are soft. Add corn and scalded milk.
Heat. This last step is important.
Just heat but do not boil. Add butter and seasonings. Serve.

title: cheese candy
directions: Toast pecans slightly.
Melt cream cheese in a double boiler; add sugar and pecans.
Mix together well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into casserole.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Serve 6.

title: ham and cheese spread
directions: Mix well.
Spread on ham.
Roll up and cut into slices.

title: salmon roll
directions: Mix together well.
Cover top with chopped pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Combine milk and ground chuck.
Divide into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, pat each into a 6-inch circle.
Place some cooked stuffing on each and draw meat over and seal.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in casserole.
Mix Ritz crackers and butter.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add chili, garlic, cumin, salt and pepper.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes and cucumbers; then mix Fritos and cheese.
Serve with chunky salsa or Ranch dressing.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place graham crackers (whole) on jelly roll pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and spread on crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm. Check when baking, will burn very easily.

title: diabetic fruit bars
directions: Boil dates,
prunes
and raisins in water.
Add butter. Mix eggs, soda, salt, flour, vanilla and nuts.	Let fruit cool before adding flour
mixture.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
If
you
want
spicy
bars
add
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.

title: man's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill one hour or more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: garlic pot roast
directions: Cut 4 of the garlic cloves into thin slivers.
Cut small slits in the roast and slide a sliver into each one.
Heat the oil in large pot and brown beef on all sides.
Remove meat.
Chop onion and remaining garlic; put into pot and cook until golden.
Return meat to pot and add wine, broth and seasonings.
Boil and reduce heat and simmer, covered for 2 1/2 hours.
Turn meat occasionally. Remove meat and keep warm.
Skim fat from liquid and bring liquid to boil until reduced to 1 1/2 cups.
Serve this sauce with roast.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain corn, beans and peas.
Mix with celery, onion and green pepper.
Boil vinegar, sugar, oil, water, pepper and paprika. Cool.
Add to vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Keeps well for a week in refrigerator.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Combine coconut and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in pureed strawberries and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm.
Before serving, garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: finger jello
directions: Heat to boil the Jell-O, cold water and sugar.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Mix together plain gelatin mixture and flavored Jell-O mixture; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until jelled; cut into desired serving pieces.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer at high speed until fluffy.
Add whipped topping, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat well.
Spoon into crust and chill 5 hours before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with butter.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Add egg yolks to mixture and mix.
Then add syrup, pecans, vanilla and salt.
Beat egg whites until they become fluffy and add to mixture.
Pour in uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It is easier to mix with hands. Shape into small balls and put on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt; add eggs, margarine, canned milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: montgomery lemon pie
directions: Line 2 pie pans with pastry.
Mix the first 5 ingredients in medium mixing bowl; beat well.
Pour into pie pans.
Mix the sugar, 2 eggs, butter, baking powder and flour in a separate bowl. Spoon over lemon mixture in pie pans.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in cake mixture.

title: mexican dip
