directions: Use a round flat dish or large pie plate.
Spread layer of bean dip, then top with avocado dip.
Mix the taco seasoning mix with sour cream and mayonnaise; spread on top of avocado dip.
Top with chopped tomatoes, onions, olives and Cheddar cheese.

I save a little Cheddar cheese and add it as a topping, just for looks. This can be made a day ahead and refrigerated or refrigerate for a couple of hours and serve with Tostitos, Fritos, tortilla chips or tacos.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Salt and pepper cut up chicken.
Place in pan in single layer. Bring the ingredients to a boil and pour over chicken.
Bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: kielbasi
directions: Brown kielbasi in large pan with peppers and onions.
Mix chili sauce with water.
Pour over kielbasi; saute 5 to 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Mix together the flour, salt, chocolate and 1/2 cup of hot water.
Fold in egg whites last.
Mix together.
Mix together the buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix as you would any cake.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: corn bread squares
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until moistened.
Spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
"I've used an iron skillet; it works good, too."
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 9 to 10 servings.

title: instant rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside. Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in Crisco.
Add lukewarm buttermilk and yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Place the amount you want to cook on floured board and knead until it's cutting out real firm.
Then pat out about 1/2-inch thick.
Let rise until double in size, about 30 minutes. Put the unused dough in bowl.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Will last several days.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until thick and lemony. Gradually add sugar while beating.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients together and carefully fold into the egg mixture by hand.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 13 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread peanut butter over hot cake. Allow to cool.
Cover with melted chocolate.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Work flour into sugar and then salt.
Add 1 cup hot water and boil three minutes.
Flavor with lemon or cinnamon.
Pour over the dumplings before baking.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 12 to 15 minutes in salted water.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop hot carrots (drained) into sauce.
Let marinate at least overnight, longer for better flavor.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix ingredients well; bake one hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions.
Drain. Combine onion, olives, eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, Parmesan cheese and American cheese and toss together. Grease a 12-cup Bundt pan with butter or margarine and lightly sprinkle with flour.
Pour macaroni mixture into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen edges with rubber spatula and invert onto serving platter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers or bread.
Hollow out or scoop out loaf of unsliced Hawaiian bread or pumpernickel bread.
Save the chunks of scooped out bread for dipping.
Serve the spinach dip in the hollowed out bread.

title: caramelized pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, flour, salt, extracts and butter and pour into the pastry shell.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes until done.
Mix the pecans, melted butter and brown sugar. Sprinkle over the top of the pie.
Place pie under the broiler until the topping is caramelized.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add 1 cup pecans.
Mix well. Refrigerate until firm and shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: stuffed hamburgers to grill
directions: Spread mustard on center of 4 hamburger patties, leaving a margin for sealing.
Top with 1 teaspoon relish; sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Place another patty on top and press edges to seal well.
Season with salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Place hamburgers on cooking grill; cook 5 to 6 minutes on each side.

title: geschnetzeltes
directions: Fry veal strips in butter.
Pour cream in pan.
Season with beef bouillon cube.
Add flour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can be made the day before and dressing added just before serving.

title: backyard baked beans(yield: 8-10 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: a dieter's dream shrimp salad
directions: Rinse shrimp and cook.
Chill can of green beans.
Drain and save liquid.
Slice thinly the garlic clove and
crush in a large bowl.
Add oil, mustard, sugar, vinegar, shrimp and beans. Refrigerate.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water to boil with butter, bouillon cubes, all soups, celery, pepper and onion about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, add chicken, broccoli, rice and all other ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: adelaide's kolaches
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine remaining ingredients with yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Let dough rise until double in size.
Punch down and turn out onto floured surface.
Knead a little.
Make small balls, flatten top and place on buttered pan. Let rise some and then take fingers and press in center to make hole for filling.
Let rise and bake at 450° until brown, about 10 minutes. Brush tops with melted butter.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Wash the berries and add them to the sugar and flour, which have been mixed together.
Pour into pastry lined pie dish.
Dot with butter or margarine in about six places so that each cut piece has the butter or margarine.
Cover with vented pastry. Press the edges together well; flute and trim.
It is very appetizing to save out some of the blueberries and decorate the top.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If canned berries are used, decrease the sugar to 1/2 cup and the flour to 2 tablespoons.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all together. Cook 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: rice torta
directions: Grind onions, garlic, a goodly amount of parsley and basilica. Add remaining ingredients and add rice.
Bake in 325° oven in 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan about 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in water just to cover for about 30 minutes, or until tender.
(You may add a bay leaf, 1/2 medium onion, sliced, and a sliced stalk of celery or two to season the stock for another use.)
Remove chicken from broth and cool enough to handle.
Then remove skin and bones and slice or break into large pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: On serving container, layer ingredients.
Serve with corn chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a glass casserole and bake, covered, at 325° for about 1 hour or until macaroni is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Will turn out a little runny.
If you want it more like a cornbread, add 2 boxes of Jiffy mix.

title: filigree cake(mother's recipe)
directions: Mix everything together in bowl and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tallerine
directions: Cook ground beef and bell pepper slowly for 25-30 minutes. Drain.
Add chili powder, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Let simmer about 5 more minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package until tender.
Mix everything together except 1/2 of the cheese. Spread remaining cheese on top and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
Pack hot into 1/2 gallon jar.
Boil sugar and vinegar.
Pour over eggs.
Add beets and juice.
Let stand overnight.
May add a few drops red food coloring.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar; cut in butter.
Press into ungreased 11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool until slightly firm before cutting into bars.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix in order given and bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.

title: apache bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make soft dough. Knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll; cut into 2-inch squares.
Fry in 1 to 2 inches of oil.
Serve hot.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Mix Good Seasons Italian salad dressing and cream cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Spread on rye party rounds. Slice cucumber and put one slice on each party round.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: In one bowl cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. In another bowl mix lemon Jell-O and water.
In another very large bowl mix whipping cream until fluffy.
Put first mixture in with whipping cream.
Mix together.
Then add Jell-O then pineapple. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Makes 3 pies.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar;
add
eggs, one at a time and beat well. Sift flour, salt and soda.	Mix food coloring with cocoa and milk; add to sugar.
Beat hard; add flour alternating with milk.	Add vanilla
and
beat	thoroughly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and
roll
into balls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy summer avocado salad
directions: Chop ripe avocados, tomatoes and onions into bite size pieces. Combine in a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and seasonings; mix gently.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time. Serves 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Melt oleo and add to stuffing mix.
Add soup, sour cream and onion to the squash. Add 1/2 of stuffing mix to squash and mix.
Put about 3/4 of remaining stuffing mix on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Put squash mixture over this.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and pineapple; mix only by hand.
Add bananas and nuts; mix again. Pour mixture into a tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let cool in pan 1 hour before removing.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix for 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake about 55 minutes at 350°.
Use 2 (9 x 5-inch) or 1 (9 x 5-inch) and 3 small pans.

title: chocolate seduction
directions: Toss the chocolate chips and the nuts in a tablespoonful of the cake mix.
Beat the remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes then fold in the chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°, or until tester inserted into cake comes out clean.
(I found it worked better in my oven to bake a little longer at 325°.)

title: corn and chicken casserole
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs in order listed.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham and navy bean vegetable soup
directions: Wash navy beans.
Add 6-8 c. water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 mins.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour. Add ham bone and cook for 1 hour, covered till meat is tender. May need more water.
Remove bone, shred meat.
Add remaining vegetables and meat.
Cook 30 mins. or till tender.
Add a few dashes of Tabasco.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in an ungreased oblong pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cake mix over pie filling.
Dump pineapple with juice. Sprinkle other half of cake mix over pineapple.
Lay pecan halves over cake mix.
Cut butter in thin squares over pecans.
Do not stir or add any liquid.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seed, flour and lemon pepper.
Dip chicken into soy sauce; dredge in sesame seed mixture.
Arrange chicken in a large, shallow baking dish.
Drizzle margarine over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: church window cookies
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Then add nuts.
Cool slightly, then add marshmallows until well coated.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and put mixture into buttered casserole.
Add milk mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Throw all ingredients in saucepan.
Mix and simmer for awhile. You're done.

title: cocoa cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except Coke and marshmallows in a large mixing bowl. Blend at low speed, then beat 1 minute at medium speed. Add Coke and blend well. Stir in marshmallows by hand.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach jell-o surprise
directions: Dissolve jell-o in water; stir and let stand.
Blend drained peach halves and cream cheese together in blender for 2 minutes. Combine jell-o and peach mixture.
Pour into dish or mold and chill until firm.
Invert onto serving dish and top with a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and serve.

title: cinnamon dumplings
directions: Place biscuits in an oblong pan; melt together brown sugar, white sugar, milk and butter and pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown. Serves 10 to 15.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs on high speed for 3 minutes. Blend in bananas. Sift flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder into mixture with spoon until well blended.
Stir in walnuts. Pour into 2 greased 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Wrap in plastic wrap when completely cooled.

title: chess pie squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and oleo and press evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together eggs, confectioners sugar and cream cheese and pour over the cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, salt and potatoes in milk.
When this mixture
is cool, add yeast cake dissolved in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Add
enough
flour	to mix to the consistency of cake batter.
Cover,
set
aside
in
warm place for 2 hours. Then
add 1 teaspoon of soda, 2 teaspoons of baking powder and 1/2 cup of flour.
Add this from sifter and mix well.	Now add enough	flour until
like biscuit dough.	Cover and set aside for
hour
in refrigerator.
Bake
rolls on greased cookie sheet at 375° until brown.
You can use only part of the dough at a time.
The rest will keep for a few days in the refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat well.
Add extracts and beat again.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: south of the border tortillas
directions: Combine pimento cheese spread and salsa. Spread about 1/4 cup of mixture into each of the tortillas. Roll up tortilla. Serve with shredded lettuce and sliced tomatoes, if desired.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt Hershey chocolate bar with almonds over double boiler. When melted, gradually stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
May garnish pie with a little of the shaved chocolate bar.
Refrigerate.

title: dilled potatoes
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add broth, potatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook until tender.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Grease
and flour bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.
Beat orange juice, eggs, oil and orange peel until mixed thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened. Stir in cranberries and nuts. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: scrambled tofu
directions: Combine entire ingredients.
Place in a Teflon or equivalent skillet over low heat, stirring consistently.
This can be served as a substitute for scrambled eggs.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In large pot, boil chicken and pork.
When tender, remove and cool, then debone, saving cooking broth in pot.
While other meat is boiling, stir-fry beef and drain grease.
Add all ingredients back in boiling pot, stir thoroughly.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with your favorite bread and salad!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook chopped broccoli in cup of water until tender; drain. Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add golden mushroom soup to broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Add cooked rice and onion; mix well. Place mixture in greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double cheese delight
directions: Brown beef and drain; add onion, celery, salt, pepper and tomato sauce and cook until vegetables are tender.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine meat mixture, sour cream and both cheeses and mix well; gently stir in cooked noodles. Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and place tomato slices on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Cook noodles by package directions and set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic in oil.
Mix together chicken pieces, "Chicken Tonight" sauce and sauteed vegetables.
Drain tomatoes and mix into chicken mixture.
Put a small amount of mixture into bottom of a long casserole dish or lasagne pan.
After draining lasagne noodles; layer noodles in a single layer in casserole dish.
Place half of chicken mixture on noodles then half of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crustless ham quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until lightly browned.
Drain and set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until well blended.

title: ranch salad dressing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients into mayonnaise.
Stir in the buttermilk.
Mix well with a wire whip.
Makes 1 quart.

title: orange julius(beverage)
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix seconds.

title: fillet of salmon au poivre
directions: In a sealable plastic bag, combine soy sauce, garlic, lemon juice and sugar.
Add salmon; coat well and let marinate, sealed and chilled for at least 30 minutes.
Remove salmon from bag (discard marinade) and press about 2 teaspoons pepper into each piece to coat.

title: homemade "egg beaters"
directions: Put all ingredients into blender jar and blend until smooth. Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Can be frozen.
Freeze in 1/4 cup amounts.
Use in place of egg in recipes or scramble.
One quarter cup is equal to 1 egg.
One quarter cup equals 80 calories.

title: butterscotch noodle treats
directions: Melt chips to soft, but not runny, stage. You'll have to use your stove to do this. Most come with an owner's manual. Add pecans. Mix in chow mein noodles. Drop by forkful onto wax paper. Chill 10 minutes minimum.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add onion, celery and pepper and cook until tender.
Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes, stirring often. Uncover and cook 15 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: white chocolate pound cake
directions: Combine chopped white chocolate and hot water in top of double boiler; bring water in bottom to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until white chocolate melts, stirring occasionally.
Let cool. Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually, add 2 1/2 cups sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Add white chocolate mixture; beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 3/4 cup milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in pecans, coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, water, oil and eggs in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix together.
Will make 2 loaves or smaller ones that can be frozen and then baked as needed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir together.
Bake in a greased casserole or 8 x 8-inch cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and egg casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole stir together the ham and the drained mushrooms.
In a mixing bowl stir together the eggs, skim milk, grated Parmesan cheese, dried parsley flakes, onion powder and pepper.
Pour the egg mixture evenly over the ham mixture in the casserole.

Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 4 to 6 minutes or until egg mixture is almost set, pushing cooked portions to center of the casserole several times during cooking. Sprinkle with the shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, 222 calories per serving.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Place
beans
in large bowl and add onion (red onion is nice) and garlic which has been put through a press.

title: herb fried chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in the salad dressing for several hours or overnight. Mix flour, salt and pepper. Drain chicken.
Dredge in flour mixture. Dip in salad dressing and roll in crumbs. Fry in hot, deep fat for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low for four hours.

title: tapioca fruit dessert
directions: Mix everything together.
Let stand 5 minutes, then bring to a boil and boil for a minute.
Take off stove and stir occasionally for 20 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: seafood dip
directions: Place cream cheese and soup in a glass bowl.
Microwave at Medium for 5 to 6 minutes or until soup and cheese are smooth, stirring every 2 minutes.
Add shrimp or crab and remaining ingredients.
Microwave at Medium for 4 additional minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.

title: smoked salmon appetizers
directions: Spread a small amount of cheese on each cracker.
Top with a thin slice of salmon.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
When ready to use, take out of freezer about 2 or 3 hours before hand.
This will make it slushy. Add 3 (28 ounce) bottles of ginger ale to mixture.

title: american perogi
directions: Boil and drain macaroni; set aside.
Boil potatoes and mash. Grate cheese and add to potatoes.
Saute onion in margarine.

title: chicken, sun-dried tomatoes and broccoli over penne
directions: Heat oil in a skillet over medium high heat.
Saute garlic until lightly browned.
Add chicken; saute for 3 minutes, then push chicken to sides of pan.
Add broccoli; saute until crisp and tender.
Add sun-dried tomatoes, crushed tomatoes, basil, red pepper, white wine and chicken broth; saute for 3 minutes.
Add butter.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cooked pasta and toss lightly.
Sprinkle with
Parmesan and serve immediately.

title: wonderful cold cucumber soup
directions: Place all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Chill 2 hours.

title: dee's best brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; set aside.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs and sugar, stirring well.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add this to chocolate mixture and stir well. Add vanilla and pecans and stir lightly.
Spray 8 x 8 pan with a little PAM.
Pour in mixture and bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees. Dust very lightly with powdered sugar while hot.
These brownies are soft and chewy.
Do not overbake.
Recipe doubles well.
Put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake 5-7 minutes longer.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: In Dutch oven, add roast and onion soup mix blended with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Continue cooking an additional 20 minutes or until beef and vegetables are tender.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: caramel turtle cake
directions: In a bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour in half of the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugars, oil and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in pumpkin.
Add water, raisins and nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes, or until done.

title: mary's holiday beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain 2 cans beans and leave juice in 1 can.
In casserole dish, mix all ingredients except bacon.
Put bacon on top.
Put in oven on cookie sheet; cover sheet with foil. Bake until bacon is crisp and beans are bubbling, about 45 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Put berries in a baking dish.
Put in the 1 1/2 cups sugar. Let stand at room temperature until juice rises.
Make a dough of the milk and flour. Roll out on a floured board. Cut in strips and lay on top of the berries lengthwise and crosswise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook and drain meat first.
Then add all other ingredients except oatmeal.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.
Add oatmeal and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or cornbread.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck, crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, allspice and 2/3 cup milk together.
Shape into meatballs, using teaspoon as measure for mixture.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add meatballs, turning frequently, brown on all sides.
Remove skillet from heat.
Sprinkle flour evenly over meatballs, stirring to blend well. Dissolve bouillon cube in water, add to meatballs.
Stir in remaining milk and Worcestershire sauce to make smooth mixture.
Return to low heat, cook until gravy is thickened.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: fried okra southern style
directions: Clean okra.
Cut crosswise into small 1/4 to 1/2-inch sections. Toss with corn meal, mixed with salt and pepper, until well coated. Fry in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels. Serve warm.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut together the flour, sugar and margarine.
Pat into a pizza pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: crunchy pecan pie
directions: In small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans and baking powder; set aside. In large bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Fold graham cracker mixture into egg whites. Spread in greased 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool completely. Spread with whipped
cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's macaroni salad
directions: Whip together the sour cream and Miracle Whip.
Stir in the milk, vinegar and mustard.
Add chopped celery and chopped onion. Stir in macaroni and cubed Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: fabulous tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add bell pepper, onion and mushrooms and saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Whisk together flour and milk until smooth; stir into vegetable mixture and cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese, stirring until melted. Stir in tuna and next 4 ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir together breadcrumbs and 2 tablespoons melted butter; sprinkle over casserole and bake 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: window cleaning solution
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water.
Combine with other ingredients and clean windows.

title: iranian yogurt soup
directions: Soak raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Drain; save water and combine with yogurt, cream, cucumber, walnuts and scallion.
Stir in raisins, salt and pepper.
Chill soup covered for 3 hours. Serve in bowls garnished with minced parsley and snipped dill.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry milk and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: lone star steaks
directions: Melt oleo and stir in all sauce ingredients.
Broil steaks, turning frequently and brushing with sauce each time you turn them. When almost done, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in egg, water and vinegar.
Mix as little as possible.
Handling will make it tough.
Tip for making baked shell: brush crust with diluted egg before cooking and filling.
It will not make crust soggy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese; add Eagle Brand milk and peanut butter.
Beat well.
Stir in lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust; swirl chocolate syrup on top.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix Hidden Valley Ranch mix and sour cream.
Add cream cheese. Beat well.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes or longer if needed.
Shape into cheese ball and roll in almonds or put in two containers without nuts and use as cracker spread.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; set aside 1 cup.
Add melted margarine. Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill in freezer 10 minutes.

title: pea cashew nut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: toll house pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and both sugars.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dream cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Butter generously a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix butter and crumbs well; reserve 1/4 cup and press remainder firmly on bottom of pan.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Gradually beat until stiff; set aside.
Beat cheese until soft.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, the flour and salt.
Gradually beat into cheese.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in egg whites and pour mixture into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup crumbs.
Bake in preheated slow oven (325°) for 1 1/4 hours or until firm.
Turn off heat, open oven door and leave cake in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand on cake rack away from drafts until cool. Chill.
(Cake will shrink some as it cools.)
Top cake with light cheesy pie filling or blueberry or pineapple.

title: cheri's laulau
directions: Spray
pan with Pam.
Line pan with ti leaves, followed by taro or luau leaves.
Place 1-inch slabs of pork butt over leaves. Sprinkle
with
a little bit of Hawaiian salt.
Add a can	of cream
of mushroom soup.
Repeat layers.
At the end, cover with ti leaves.	Cover pan; bake in a 300° oven for 6 to 8 hours.
In a big pan, use 3 cans of cream of mushroom soup.

title: date cake
directions: Pour water over dates and raisins.
Set aside.
Let soak until water cools.
Stir until thick.

title: soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven and cook for approximately 45 minutes, then you have soup.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to the egg mixture.
Beat until smooth. Test mixture to see if it flows easily through funnel. Fry at 350° until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Eat warm.

title: spiced apple aspic
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add Jell-O and candies and stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Let chill until it begins to congeal.
Add apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain and place in casserole.
Put chicken on top.
Mix mayo, lemon juice, egg and cream of chicken soup. Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Spread on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and allow top to brown.

title: heart-healthy baked fish
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Place fairly thick layer of sliced or chopped onions on pan.
Place fish fillets on onions. Sprinkle with lemon juice and spices.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.

title: baked egg and tomato casserole
directions: Butter a casserole.
Butter bread on both sides and cover bottom of dish.
Break in eggs.
Season (do not break the yolks). Cover with another layer of buttered bread.
Season and strain tomatoes and pour over all.
Bake 45 minutes in slow oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes with melted butter and sugar.
Whip in the eggs. Add spices, milk and part of coconut.
(Save a little coconut to sprinkle on top.)
Mix well and pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with coconut and bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: fudgy peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add combined 1 cup flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining 1 cup flour and peanut butter chips.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes or until firm.
Remove immediately.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken burritos
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover in saucepan until tender. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup broth.
Bone and chop chicken.
Combine chicken, broth and next 3 ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix flour, baking powder, oil, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add water, mixing to form a ball.
Divide into ten portions.
Roll each portion into a circle on floured surface.

title: creamy cucumber slices
directions: Mix salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Add sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in onions, parsley and cucumber slices. Arrange on flat dish.

title: burger best(deluxe hamburger)
directions: Beat eggs well. Add parsley, oregano, pepper and salt. Blend well with ground beef. Form into patties of 4+ ounces each. Broil to taste or bake on rack in pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve on bakery semi-hard roll with chopped fresh onions and usual condiments on the side.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix real good and pour into baking pan.
Spread a little ketchup on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together the broccoli, water chestnuts, Cheddar cheese, celery, onion, bacon and raisins.
Add dressing made of the mayonnaise, cider vinegar and sugar.
Mix and chill for 2 hours in order for the flavor to develop before serving.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans (may be doubled).
Press in a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; add to first layer.
Blend Jell-O pudding and milk; add to second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all but crackers well.
Pour over crackers well.
Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
No cooking.
Store in container for freshness.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar; add butter and bring to boil over medium heat.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, slowly.
Stir in pecans.
Remove from heat and add rum slowly.
Pour into 9 inch baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy mexicali dinner
directions: Cook meat and onion in large skillet until onion is tender. Stir in noodles, tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 cup cheese, olives and seasonings.
